title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well all ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: date squares
directions: Mix all together and bake in an 8-inch square pan.
Cut in squares while still warm.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into small balls and bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mexican lasagna casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add garlic, tomatoes, salt and taco seasoning.
Set aside.
Combine egg, cottage cheese and Cheddar cheese.

title: blueberry batter pudding
directions: Pick over and wash berries.
Put in shallow baking dish. Sprinkle
with
lemon
juice.
Cream
together
butter, 1/2 cup sugar,
egg
and vanilla until well blended.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into mixture.
Spread over berries.
Mix 1/3
cup
sugar,
cornstarch, cinnamon and lemon rind.
Stir in boiling
water.
Pour over blueberry mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes
or until golden brown and pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm, plain or with cream, if used.

title: butterflied southern citrus barbecue
directions: Place lamb in large glass or enamel bowl.
In measuring cup, combine remaining ingredients; pour over lamb.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Drain lamb, reserving marinade.

Grill lamb 4 to 6 inches above coals or source of heat for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until meat thermometer inserted in thickest part registers 140° for rare or 150° to 155° for medium. Baste with marinade.

title: glazed ham
directions: Boil to soften skin.
Cover with water; take off skin.
Score fat, then add cloves to each score.
Add brown sugar to cover ham. Pour juice from pineapple can over ham.
Decorate with pineapple. During baking baste often.
Towards end pour 1/4 to 1/2 cup of Log Cabin or any maple syrup.
Mix cornstarch and water into a paste, then pour into pan drippings.
Add Gravy Master or Kitchen Bouquet.

title: nanny schembre's favorite ratatouille
directions: Lightly saute garlic and onions in olive oil.
Dust vegetables with flour, except tomatoes.
Add vegetables to skillet along with tomatoes, salt, pepper, parsley, oregano and basil.
Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Stir, turn heat down to low and simmer 1 hour.
Serve as a side vegetable or cold as a salad for lunch.

title: ann's meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except olive oil; mix well (use hands).
Roll into golf ball size balls.
Saute in olive oil until lightly browned.
Add to sauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: To lighten recipe, you can substitute Egg Beaters for eggs and 1 cup applesauce for 1 cup oil.
It turns out just as good.

title: cinch sugar cookies
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix. Mix together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well together.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar, sugar and cinnamon, sugar and cocoa or nuts to make a variety.
Put on sheets; flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
I check often after 7 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken or 1 package of chicken breasts.
Debone and cut in small pieces and put in casserole.
Mix together milk, chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
(Do not dilute chicken soup.) Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle corn stuffing on top and pour melted oleo on.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple and nut cake
directions: Beat together vegetable oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Mix well. Add nuts and raw apples.
Bake at 350° in tube pan for 1 hour.

title: springerle(christmas cookies)
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl; gradually add sugar and continue beating until mixture is thick and light in color (10 to 15 minutes).
Add anise flavoring and dry ingredients gradually. When too stiff for mixer, knead by hand using ample flour if sticky.
Divide dough in half; roll out and make impressions with springerle rolling pin or board (dough should be about 1/2-inch thick).
Cut cookies apart and place on cookie sheets lined with smooth kitchen towels.
Let stand overnight to set designs.
Bake at 275° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Tops should be white, bottom yellowish, but not brown.
When cool, store in airtight container. (A slice of apple in container will help keep them soft.)

title: cheese crisps
directions: Form small balls and press flat with fork onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix eggs and oranges.
Beat 3 minutes.
Add dry ingredients. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Trim fat off meat. Mix other ingredients in bottom of a large crockpot; add meat. Cook on high for 4 hr., then reduce to low and continue to cook for 4-5 hrs. more. Take meat out and shred. Return meat to crockpot (leave other ingredients in crockpot meat will absorb juices after being shredded) and keep warm until serving time. If there is too much liquid on the meat discard some. May be frozen. May also be made with venison instead of pork.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, soup mix and 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Press into loaf pan.
To remaining tomato sauce, add 1/2 can of water and 2 tablespoons of brown sugar.
Pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix together vinegar, sugar and cornstarch.
Grind zucchini or squash coarse and mix salt in lightly.
Let stand in icebox overnight.
Add zucchini to mixture and heat until boiling.
Stir all the time.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.
Good on hot dogs, hamburgers and with beans.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add sifted flour and soda.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Make into little balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Dip fork into sugar and press down "crisscross".
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cookies will be soft.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans and toss
together
with
green
pepper and onion. Mix together sugar, oil, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and salt.
Boil for 5
minutes and pour hot dressing over bean mixture.
Mix well.
Refrigerate
several
hours
before serving. May reduce sugar
if desired.
Keeps in refrigerator for several days.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Melt one stick of butter in pan.
Pour over butter.
Pour one can of sliced peaches in middle.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken mornay
directions: Season the chicken and place in an ovenproof dish.
Dot with 2 ounces of the butter and bake in the center of the oven at 400° for 20 minutes.
Make the white sauce.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown ground meat.
Cook onion and pepper until soft.
Add to meat the onion, pepper, taco seasoning, tomato paste and refried beans.
Cook 1/2 hour in skillet, stirring often.
Place in casserole dish and top with shredded cheese.
Bake until melted. Top with layer of sour cream before serving.

title: baked lemon pudding(low-fat, low sugar)
directions: You will need vegetable cooking spray.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream crisco, sugar and eggs together for approximately 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well.
Add flavoring and mix.
Add remaining flour and milk.
Continue to mix well.
Grease and flour 2 round pans.
Bake at 350 degrees approximately 20 minutes until done.

title: mom's strawberry pie(makes 2)
directions: Cook the water, sugar and cornstarch together until thick and boils.
Then add jello.
Mix well and remove from stove.
Let set until cool.
After mixture is cool, add to sliced strawberries. Pour into 2 baked pie shells and refrigerate.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and brown sugar first, then add vanilla eggs and water.
Make sure beaten well, then add dry ingredients. Last, add chocolate chips and nuts if you want.
Bake at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a clean flower pot, plastic flower and gummy worms.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients and shape into balls.
Freeze.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: hot cheese balls
directions: Mix all in a large bowl; add milk if needed to roll in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: golden cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and margarine together. Beat in egg yolks.
Add vanilla and baking soda in water and mix. Next, add cream of tartar.
Finally, add flour and mix well.
Take 1/2 teaspoon of mixture and roll into size of marble.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: fruitcake
directions: Sift together both types of flour, setting aside 1 cup to roll raisins in.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a bowl, combine the salmon (I remove the bones), onion, crackers and egg.
Mix to bind well.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chili powder.
Form into a log and chill until firm.
Roll into chili powder to make a light coating.
Slice thin and serve on crackers.
This can be frozen.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Soften jello in water.
Combine other ingredients.
Bake in 3 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water;
set aside. Mix dry
ingredients;
cut in shortening until the consistency of corn
meal.
Add
buttermilk
and
yeast;
mix
well.
Add little extra
flour
and
knead.
Place in tight container and refrigerate.
Will	keep for several days.	When ready to use, roll out and
cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise in warm place 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Over low flame, stir in all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with wedges of green pepper which have been boiled with 3 garlic cloves and salt for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle heavily with grated cheese (Cheddar).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 12 +.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry
ingredients
in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients (except
boiling
water);
beat
at medium speed 2 minutes.
Add
boiling
water.
Ingredients
of batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350°: two 9-inch pans or 3 (8-inch) pans 30 to 35 minutes,
one 13 x 9-inch pan 35
to	40
minutes
or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat slowly. Drain fat.
Add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes, tomato paste and 1 cup water. Simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Stir often.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water.
Drain and rinse.
Beat eggs.
Add Ricotta, Parmesan, parsley and pepper.
Spray 13 x 9 pan with cooking spray.
Layer half noodles and spread with half Ricotta mixture. Add half Mozzarella cheese and half meat sauce. Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.	Let stand 10 minutes before serving or assemble early and refrigerate.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes and let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: graham cracker delights
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Break crackers apart and place on cookie sheet.
In a small saucepan, combine butter and margarine.
Melt; add sugar and bring to a boil for 2 minutes. Pour over graham crackers, covering all of crackers.
Sprinkle with pecans, chopped fine.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes.
Watch closely; burns easily.

title: spinach crust
directions: Drain spinach in a colander and squeeze in a towel or with hands to remove all moisture.
In a small pan melt butter, stir in spinach and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in milk and egg.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour the soup/wine mixture over the chicken.
Sprinkle the grated cheese over all this and cover loosely with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: rhubarb upside down cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
On bottom of pan, put layer of rhubarb.
Sprinkle on sugar.
Add marshmallows; then sprinkle on Jell-O.
Top with cake mix that has been made into batter as directed on package.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Serve hot with whipping cream or ice cream.

title: fruit punch
directions: Empty frozen concentrates, pineapple and cranberry juices and water into a large container.

Let stand until frozen juice is thawed; stir well. Pour mixture into punch bowl; add ice cubes. Just before serving, gently pour in ginger ale and club soda. Garnish with Fruit Ice Ring, fruit and mint leaves. Yield: 25 to 30 servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown the smoked sausage. Drain grease. Add cooked sausage back to skillet. Add remaining ingredients to skillet. Boil then simmer. Serve over cooked rice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
shortening
and	sugar;	add eggs and beat well. Add remaining ingredients.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Measure the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, oil, eggs and vanilla in the order listed in a large mixing bowl.
Blend 1 minute on low speed, then 2 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in the carrots, nuts and raisins.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch greased bottom only square pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: fresh blackberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add sugar mixture to blackberries; toss to coat fruit.
Fill a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate with berry mixture.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edge.

title: christmas cookies(these could be called fruitcake cookies)
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add combined cinnamon, salt, soda and flour.
Stir in fruits and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple frosting for 2-layer cake
directions: Stir pudding and pineapple, then add Cool Whip.
Do not beat; just stir together.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half.
Cook and drain.
While still warm, combine spaghetti with eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Pour into well-greased deep dish pie pan.
Spoon sour cream over spaghetti. Cook ground beef; drain.
Add tomato paste, salt and water; simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon ground beef on top of sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese, then return to oven until cheese melts.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello, pudding and boiling water.
Let cool. Add whipped Dream Whip.
After mixture has cooled, add frozen strawberries and bananas.

title: neptune's cheese canapes(microwave appetizer recipe)
directions: *Substitution:
Can use package of imitation crab or can of tuna instead of crabmeat.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
Prepare sauce with the sauce and hamburger.
In a sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan, layer sauce, noodles, Swiss and Mozzarella cheese slices and cottage or Ricotta cheese until pan is full.
Put in oven at 350° until bubbly, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening together; add sugar and beat well. Add eggs beating after each one.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add coconut flavoring; beat well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
After cake cools, remove from pan; mix 1/2 glass of milk with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix well and pour over cake (pierce holes in cake so milk mixture can soak into cake).

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix real well the sugar, chocolate and flour together in a pan.
Add milk slowly.
Cook on medium heat.
When thickening starts, add butter and stir.
Cook until desired thickness.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: skillet chicken risotto
directions: In 10-inch skillet, brown chicken on all sides in hot oil, about 15 minutes.
Remove chicken pieces.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add rice, onion, salt and poultry seasoning. Cook and stir until rice is lightly browned.
Add mushrooms, carrots and water.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Season chicken with additional salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with paprika, cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chicken and rice are tender. Serves 4 to 6.

title: teriyaki salmon
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place salmon fillets on rack in broiling pan.
In cup mix teriyaki sauce, ginger root and sesame oil. Brush mixture over salmon fillets.
Broil salmon 3 to 5 inches from source of heat, without turning until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork, about 10 minutes.
Garnish with parsley sprigs.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute together ground beef, chopped onion and bell pepper. Add tomatoes, red beans and seasonings.
Simmer about 1 hour and serve over rice.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and cocoa in double boiler until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in eggs.
Add to butter and cocoa. Preheat oven to 350° and cook for 30 to 35 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sliced apples in greased oblong pan (9 x 13-inch).
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with Cool Whip, milk or ice cream.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve with crackers or on lettuce leaf.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients using half of the cheese in the batter. Pour into a large, greased skillet.
Sprinkle with other half of cheese.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: perfect barbecue ribs
directions: Light grill and allow coals to get white hot.
Lightly spray ribs with olive oil spray on both sides.
Season ribs on both sides with salt, pepper, garlic and onion.
Grill ribs on both sides until evenly brown, placing cover on grill after each turning to add smoked flavor to the ribs.
Place browned ribs in a roasting pan lined with foil.
You may also use a disposable foil pan.
Add about 1 1/2 cups of water to ribs and lightly pour or brush on your favorite barbecue sauce over ribs.
Cover ribs with foil and place in a 325° oven for 1 to 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream crumbs
directions: Mix together and bake for 30 minutes in preheated oven.
Great with summer drinks.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil together until fluffy.
Add shredded zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients together, add to egg mixture.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt. Add tortellini and cook until al dente.
Do not overcook.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Meanwhile, cook the vegetables according to package directions in boiling water or microwave. When done, rinse under cold water and drain well.
In large serving bowl, stir together the olive oil, garlic salt and oregano.
Add cooked tortellini and vegetables.
Stir gently to coat with dressing.
If salad seems dry, add a little more olive oil.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in an 8-inch square pan. Top with your choice of 1/2 cup of nuts and/or 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This recipe can easily be doubled.

title: honey pecan butter
directions: Beat butter until smooth and soft.
Beat in honey, then mix in pecans.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar and salt in pie plate.
Mix together a little the milk and oil.
Add (pour) on flour mix in pie plate.
Mix with a fork and press into shape around pie plate. Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, baking soda, salt, shortening, peanut butter, milk, vanilla and egg at low speed until stiff dough forms.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.

Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately top each cookie with a candy kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edge; remove from cookie sheets. Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix together oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and soda.
Cut in butter.
Put 2/3 (about 4 2/3 cups) of crumb mixture into a greased 12 x 8 x 2 inch pan.
Press down firmly.
Spread with filling. Sprinkle with rest of crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: e. z. toasty bread
directions: Slice bread lengthwise.
Mix together margarine and onions. Spread on each 1/2 of bread.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, spread side up.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Slice into serving size pieces.

title: tuna noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles as label directs.
Mix tuna, soup, milk, pepper and noodles.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Mix water, tomato paste, and sauce.
Put in a crock pot.
Add all seasonings, onion, and garlic.
Add 1/4 c. red wine and 1/4 c. romano cheese.
Turn crock pot on high and start cooking.
Fry hamburger and sausage till brown, drain.
Add to sauce.
Cook on high for 4 hours.
Let cool.
Take out inside part of crock pot and refrigerate over night.
Put back in crock pot next day and heat to serving temperature.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti using package directions.
Drain.
Place spaghetti in large bowl.
Add onion, tomato, cucumbers, green pepper and Salad Supreme seasoning.
Mix well.
Add desired amount of salad dressing.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar in a large bowl and set aside.
In a separate bowl, mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip and add mixture to the cream cheese mixture.
Crush Oreo cookies in food processor until fine.

title: miss inez's pineapple casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except for bread and butter.
Melt butter and crumble bread in the melted butter and pat this mixture on top of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cat-head biscuits
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients
in
a
medium bowl; add milk mixture
and
oil.
Stir
until
moistened.
Add a little more flour and turn dough over in bowl.
Pour some oil in an 8-inch round baking pan.
Oil hands and spoon a large amount of dough in hands
and
form
a ball.
Place in pan and pat with oiled hands. Make
5 biscuits.
Place in preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: low-fat jello cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box. Make vanilla pudding using skim milk. Make Jell-O using 1/2 the water needed (don't chill). Once cake cools, poke holes using a fork. Pour the Jell-O into the holes. Spread with vanilla pudding and then Cool Whip. Chill and serve. Makes 12 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix the ingredients; spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
After done, brush warm biscuits with:

title: cocktail smokies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook slow on low, stirring often.
Add ingredients to taste.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together; shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in a shallow, greased pan for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve as appetizers.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Cover beans by 1 inch and soak.
Drain beans, recover with water, add meat bones and cook until tender.*
Fry bacon and onion in olive oil, add to beans.
Thinly slice chorizo, add to beans. Add diced potatoes, ham, salt and saffron.
Cook to desired consistency.

title: green (spinach) pasta
directions: Cook the spinach following directions on the package.
Drain it.
Let it cool slightly.
Squeeze it as dry as possible and chop it finely.
Put flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center and in it put the eggs, salt and spinach.
Mix together with your fingers and knead until smooth, adding more flour or a few drops of water as necessary.

title: nonie's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, eggs, milk, soda, salt, corn, and oil; set aside. Brown ground meat; drain and set aside. Grease a skillet for baking; sprinkle a thin layer of corn meal and let brown. Pour 1/2 corn meal mixture into skillet; sprinkle in meat, cheese, onions, and jalapeno peppers. Add remaining corn meal mixture over filling. Bake at 350° until done.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse.
While the preceding cooks, brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper.
When done, mix macaroni and beef mixture together.
Add together the pizza sauce, tomato paste, tomato sauce and 1/2 tablespoon sugar.
Mix all together.
Add several dashes of garlic salt, onion salt and oregano.
Place 1/2 mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Add remainder of mixture; top with rest of Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gameburger rice supper
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in the oil until soft.
Add ground meat and saute until it loses its color.
Stir in remainder of ingredients.
Save cheese and heat to a boil.
Turn down and simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top when ready to serve.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Take slice of ham. Spread on cream cheese. Slice pickles lengthwise. Put enough pickle on end of slice of ham. Roll up and cut into small pieces. Insert toothpick for easy handling.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers. Cut into rings. Remove seeds. Soak 24 hours in 2 cups pickling lime and 8 1/2 quarts water. Drain cucumber rings and wash off lime water. Pour cold water over them and let stand 3 hours. Drain. Simmer 2 hours in 1 cup of vinegar, food coloring and alum, with enough water to cover them. Drain.

title: mom's apple or peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 17 x 11 x 2 1/2-inch baking pan.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening into flour until it resembles coarse meal.
Add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn on floured board.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out dough in large rectangle (1/4-inch thick).
Sprinkle apples and cinnamon over dough evenly.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Dampen edges with water to seal.
Slice dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Place in pan of melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls.
This looks like too much liquid, but crust will absorb it.
Bake approximately 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.
You may dot some butter and sprinkle some sugar on top after it bakes awhile.

title: jello
directions: Sprinkle graham crackers on top.

title: slickers(dumplings)
directions: Mix flour and all dry ingredients together.
Mix in shortening and then buttermilk and make stiff dough.
Roll thin and cut into strips.
Drop in boiling broth. Cook until done.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
In a large kettle, bring water to a boil.
Cook peppers for 5 minutes.
Remove and drain. Cook rice according to package directions.
In a skillet brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, herbs, salt and pepper. Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Stuff peppers with rice mixture. Place upright in shallow pan (baking dish).
Bake at 375° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.
Leftover peppers will freeze well.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Drain sauerkraut (do not wash), cut in small pieces and add other ingredients.
Mix well and allow to marinate for 24 hours.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook in salted water the fettuccine according to package; drain. Add butter. Mix heavy cream, eggs and cheese. Pour over pasta. Add parsley and mix well. Serve.

title: southern blackberry cobbler
directions: Place blackberries in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt, mixing well.
Sprinkle over blackberries.
Dot with butter.

title: great grandmother's pound cake
directions: Beat the butter to a cream.
Stir in the sugar.
Add the yolks of the eggs, then the rose water.
Stir well.
Add the flour and stir until light.
Stir in the well beaten egg whites.
Pour into the pan and bake slowly (300°) until a light brown (about 2 hours).

title: icebox cookies
directions: Combine.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Put in buttered bread pans.
Leave in icebox overnight.
Turn from pan and cut loaf lengthwise, then cut in thin slices.
Bake on cookie sheet at 450° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Boil cocoa, sugar, butter and milk 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Slowly stir in oatmeal. Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.

title: artichokes
directions: Combine all ingredients except artichokes in 5-quart pot and bring to a boil.
Add artichokes, partially cover with lid and return to boil.
Cook until stem end easily pierced with a fork, allowing 30 minutes for medium or 40 minutes for large artichokes. Remove from liquid and drain upside down.
Serve hot or cold. May be served with melted butter or mayonnaise for dipping.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 teaspoons of sugar. Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, condensed milk and lime juice in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 160° (about 10 minutes).
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves (2 to 4 minutes).
Pour hot filling into pie shell. Immediately spread meringue over filling, sealing to edge.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch pans.
Cut in squares and garnish to serve.
Also serves well just being chilled well.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: *Or use 1 bouillon cube dissolved in 1 1/4 cups boiling water. If converted rice is used, reduce water but bouillon cube can still be added.

title: pasta pizza
directions: Add pepperoni, mushrooms, peppers and onions.
Top with cheeses.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: buffalo drumsticks
directions: Combine garlic, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, oil, pepper sauce and paprika in a small bowl and mix well.
Dip each drumstick in mixture, coating well and arrange in a single layer in a shallow glass dish.
Pour any extra sauce over the top. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate overnight.
Let chicken return to room temperature before cooking.

title: chicken ziegenfuss
directions: Boil chicken with celery and onions for 1 hour or until done. Strain celery and onions from broth.
Save enough broth for sauce. Let chicken cool and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, cream cheese, green onion and 1/4 cup margarine.
Roll crescent rolls into 8 square pieces.
Put 1/8 cream cheese mixture on each roll.
Roll up and pinch ends closed.
Dip each in 1/4 cup melted margarine and then nuts.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: taco delight
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together in skillet.
Chop tomatoes and lettuce in large pan.
Crush Fritos.
Grate cheese.
When ready to eat, add cheese to lettuce and tomatoes mix, add hamburger mixture, mix and then add Fritos.
Mix everything completely and eat while warm.
You can adjust the amounts of the ingredients to suit your taste.
Serves a crowd.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in pot; stir in flour, mixing well.
Add milk; stir, until combined with flour, over medium heat.
Add cream cheese and heat until melted.
Pour into casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.
(Adjust the amount of peppers to your own taste.
We like it hotter.)

title: pickled beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a crock.
Let stand 4 days.

title: light and heavenly
directions: Mix the flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into a 3-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool.
This makes the crust.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Make the cake and pudding.
Make layers of pudding, cake and Cool Whip.
Top with chocolate sprinkles and cherries.

title: play dough
directions: Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until the mixture forms a ball.
Let cool, knead it a bit to smooth it out.
Store this play dough in plastic bags in the refrigerator.
Can leave out food coloring and divide dough into portions and knead a few drops of different food coloring into each portion.

title: korean salad dressing for spinach salad
directions: Whisk together the ingredients and pour over your salad.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix cornbread as per package directions.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach fluff
directions: Put peaches in blender and chop well. Add dry pudding mix and light Cool Whip; chill.

title: cinnamon date rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, yeast and salt.
Heat water, 1/2 cup milk and 1/2 cup butter until very warm (125° to 130°).
Stir into dry ingredients.
Mix in eggs and enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 4 to 6 minutes.
Cover.
Let rest 10 minutes.

title: chicken soraya(persian)
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Let stand 20 minutes. Pound chicken breasts a little to flatten.
Spread butter thickly along wide part of breast.
Sprinkle apricot slivers over butter. Roll breasts tightly around filling.
Dip rolled chicken in flour, then egg.
Pack bread crumbs around chicken so they adhere.
Melt small amount of butter in heavy skillet and brown breaded chicken (about 5 minutes on each side).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put chicken in pan; put rice over.
Mix together both soups and chicken broth and pour over rice.
Pour dressing over and bake until brown.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Use a glass dish, not metal or plastic.
Cover and place in refrigerator 2 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade and cook on grill.
Yields 8 servings.

title: brownies
directions: In top of deep double boiler, put butter and chocolate; melt and blend together.
Turn off heat and add sugar (use only 1 1/2 cups if you want a little more chocolaty brownie).
When slightly cooled, add eggs and beat well.
Add scant cup of unsifted flour and beat well.
Add a bit of cinnamon, real vanilla and salt; mix well.
Add chopped nuts or some raisins, if desired.
Turn into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
For soft-type brownies, bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
For chewy ones, bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: microwave chocolate pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt in a medium size glass bowl.
Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring once half-way through cooking time.
Microwave on High until mixture is cooked and thickened, about 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in butter or margarine and vanilla.
Pour into individual serving dishes.
Press plastic wrap directly onto surface of pudding.
Chill.
Serves 4.

title: nutritious and delicious oatmeal cookies
directions: *Nuts may be chopped and mixed into dough or halves (or quarters) may be placed on top, pushing down to flatten cookie.

title: oatmeal pudding cookies
directions: Combine in mixer the butter, sugars, eggs and pudding; beat well.
Pour into large bowl.
Add all dry ingredients; mix well. Roll out in small balls and press.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: baked beans and hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Use 1/2 of this mix to coat crust.
Add 1 quart vanilla ice cream, softened.
Drizzle other half of fudge mix over top and freeze.
Take out 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cake doughnuts
directions: Sift together 3 times the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix brown sugar, eggs, mashed potatoes, milk, oil and nutmeg.
Then mix together with flour.
Dough will be sticky.
Roll out on board with as little flour as possible.
Cut and fry in deep fat until pops up, turn and remove from fryer.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour and salt in heavy saucepan.
Add milk slowly.
Stir and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boiling point.
Add to well beaten egg yolks; continue cooking to desired thickness for pie.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Spread the whipped cream on top.
Sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: raspberry-blueberry sauce
directions: Mix 1 cup of the raspberries, the preserves, water and sugar in a medium sized heavy saucepan (not uncoated aluminum).
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Strain mixture through fine strainer suspended over bowl.
Press down on raspberries to release juice.
Discard seeds.
Stir blueberries and remaining 1 cup of raspberries into hot raspberry syrup.
Cover and let stand until cool.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, cut in shortening and milk.
Stir with fork to mix.
Turn out on floured board and knead a few times. Roll out and cut.
Place on greased baking sheet or shallow metal baking pan.
Bake at 425° to 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook (can be steamed) carrots until tender, but still crunchy. Mix all other ingredients and add to carrots.
Refrigerate, the longer the better.

title: crescent cordon bleu
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Grease large cookie sheet.	In medium bowl, combine chicken, ham, mushrooms, and cheese.	Separate dough into 8 rectangles.	Spoon rounded 1/2 cup of meat mixture onto center of each rectangle of dough.	Pull 4 corners of dough to center;
twist slightly and seal edges.
Place on prepared cookie sheet.
Brush with egg; sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake for 18 to 24 minutes.
To reheat leftovers: wrap loosely in foil and place in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until warm. Serves 4.

title: oyster mosca
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients until soft and clear.
Blend in the rest of the ingredients.
Place about 8 raw oysters (depending on size) in serving dish.
Pour mixture over oysters and bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Dump all ingredients, except cornflakes and 1/4 cup oleo, into a big casserole dish.
Mix and top with crushed cornflakes or crackers.
Pour 1/4 cup melted oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mamie's blueberry molasses cake
directions: Beat. Add 1 cup boiling water. Beat, then fold in blueberries. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: curried fruit, vegetable and meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Turn out into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Form into a loaf. Bake for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours until well browned on outside. Serve with parsley potatoes and a salad.

title: potage daquise
directions: Drain beets; chop and put back in liquid.
Add boiling water and chopped onion.
Add and season with remaining ingredients. Chill.
Whisk in some sour cream.
Fold in garnish.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Cook zucchini with sliced/chopped onion and about 1 tablespoon margarine.
Add seasoned salt to taste.
In a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish layer a couple of spoons of Ragu sauce, some noodles, cooked ground beef, Ragu sauce, zucchini mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake (350°) or microwave uncovered 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: onion ring chicken
directions: Combine oleo, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard and salt to your taste.
Crush onion rings.
Dip chicken breast in sauce, then roll in onion rings.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes in uncovered pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 1 hour at 350°. One pound of sausage can be added to this recipe.
Another variation is to add 1 package of meat seasoning mix.

title: fancy fruit compote
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.
Crumble 1/2 macaroons onto bottom.
Pour all fruits on top.
Melt butter and wine together and pour on fruit.
Sprinkle almonds; crumble remaining macaroons and sprinkle on, then sprinkle brown sugar. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells until almost done; drain. Brown hamburger; drain. Mix mushrooms, onions, garlic, shredded cheese, eggs and Ricotta. Sprinkle Parmesan (to your taste). Pour spaghetti sauce in a 9 x 13 (or bigger) pan. Stuff mixture in shells, then cover with Mozzarella and sprinkle Parmesan on top. Dish is ready when the cheese is melted and sauce is bubbling over cheese.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Sprinkle on top of sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: puffs
directions: Combine butter and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add flour and stir.
Will form into a ball.
Remove from burner.
Add one egg at a time and mix well.
Drop 1/2 tsp. to 1 tsp. on cookie sheet. Bake at 400 degrees for 20 - 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until well mixed.
Add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add apples and raisins and stir gently with a strong spoon.
Spread batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: seafood spread
directions: Spread
cream cheese on a platter. Spread cocktail sauce on cream cheese.
Boil shrimp in water and crab boil.
Add Tony's seasoning to water. Let cool.
Chop in food processor and sprinkle on top of cocktail sauce.
Add crabmeat then shallots. Serve with crackers.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems (chop stems).
In a skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil, sausages, chopped stems and garlic.
Cook until lightly browned.
In a bowl, mix cheese, parsley and bread crumbs.
Add mixture in skillet with meat and toss.
Fill mushrooms and sprinkle with remaining oil.
Put on cookie sheet and bake for 25 minutes in oven preheated to 350°.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, salt, pepper, Parmesan cheese, parsley and garlic well.
Dip chicken pieces in butter and then in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken pieces so they do not touch in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: zucchini and rice terrine
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Oil a loaf pan or 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook rice in plenty of boiling, salted water 10 to 15 minutes and drain.
Chop onion and zucchini.
Mince garlic.
Heat the oil in a large frying pan and cook onion over medium-low heat until soft. Add zucchini and garlic and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix together and make a long roll; put in waxed paper.
Chill overnight, then cut and put on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Dip in powdered sugar while hot.
Let cool, then dip in powdered sugar again.

title: green beans italian
directions: Place beans in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle onion over beans.
Arrange stewed tomatoes
evenly over onion.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Take remaining cake mix, add and dot over top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour for 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly. Pour into a greased 1-quart baking dish. Bake 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place ground beef in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Salt and pepper ground beef.
Place a layer of thinly sliced onions over ground beef.
Place a layer of thinly sliced potatoes over onions. Salt potatoes.
Alternate layers of onions and potatoes.
Pour mushroom soup on top.
Do not add water.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours
or until potatoes are tender.

title: pecan millionaires
directions: Melt caramels and milk in microwave until creamy.
(Check often.)
Stir pecans in melted caramels.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and chill.
Melt chocolate bark; dip candy in chocolate mixture, using toothpick.
Place on wax paper until set.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Divide ingredients
in	order
to
use	food processor; make twice.
Have
cheese
and
margarine at room temperature. Mix in food processor:
1	cup
flour,
1/2 stick margarine, 8 ounces cheese, 1/2 teaspoon paprika, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon red pepper.
Process
until it makes soft dough.
Add whole pecans; process until chopped.

title: raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for topping.
To remaining mixture, add baking powder, soda, salt, sour cream, 1 egg and extract.
Blend well.
Spread batter over bottom and up sides (2 inches) of pan.

title: spanish noodles
directions: For the noodles, mix together eggs, salt and enough flour to make very stiff dough.
Roll out very thin and allow to stand in cool place for 3 or 4 hours.
Roll up and slice very thin.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Slice the sweet potatoes thin and place in a large skillet (electric skillet works well). Add sugar, margarine and water to cover sweet potatoes about halfway. Add orange juice, if desired. Cover and simmer on low heat until done.
Add water as needed.

title: edna cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time alternately with flour until all ingredients have been mixed. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°, then increase heat to 400° for remaining ten minutes.
Do not open oven during baking time.
Let cool in pan 20 minutes. Turn top side up on plate.
Extra good cake!

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix cream cheese in a bowl, then chop meat and green onions. Mix well.
Chop olives and mushrooms.
Mix together.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: zesty tomato mac and beef
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Drain, season with salt and pepper if desired.
Add undrained tomatoes and water; bring to a boil.
Stir in macaroni. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until pasta is cooked.
Stir in cheese. Garnish with sliced green onions and sour cream if desired.

title: marinated flank steak(london broil)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over flank steak; marinate overnight.
Grill and slice on the bias for most tender meat.

title: stir and drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat together the 2 eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir in sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass bottom oiled and dipped in sugar.
(I bake without flattening.)
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vidalia onion rings
directions: Slice onions 1/8 inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar and add ice water to cover.
Soak for 1 hour.
Make batter of flour, salt, water, vegetable oil and beaten egg whites.
Drain onion rings and dip into batter.
Fry at 375° until brown.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Blend all together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of filling.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce to 350° and bake until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean, 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Delicious, tastes like sugar cream pie.

title: aunt martha's sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef with onion and celery until meat loses its red color.
Remove excess fat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash, peel, core and slice apples.
Combine apples and cider in 6-quart pot.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover, stirring occasionally.
Simmer until apples are tender (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).
Puree apples in blender until smooth.
Return apple mixture to pot.
Add sugar, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Bring to boil over medium low heat.
Cover and cook until thick (approximately 1 hour).
Pour into canning jars, leaving 1/4-inch space.
Cover jar with lids and deep boil jars for 10 minutes.
Cool jars 10 to 12 hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni for about 7 minutes and drain.
Brown ground beef, salt, pepper and onions and drain.
Mix all of the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: low-fat trifle
directions: Prepare sugar-free vanilla pudding using skim milk.
In a glass bowl layer cake, pudding and fruit.
Top with low-fat whipping cream, like Cool Whip or Reddi-Wip.

title: no bake lemony cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water and set aside.
In a medium bowl, beat cream cheese with electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually beat in dissolved gelatin.
Fold whipped topping into cheese mixture and spoon into crust.
Chill 4 hours or until firm.
Serve topped with cherry pie filling.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken until done and chop.
Mix together 2 cans of mushroom soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and all other seasonings.

Fill each tortilla with mixture, placing a toothpick through each to hold together, then place in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish. Mix last can of mushroom soup and sour cream together until blended smooth.
Spoon over enchiladas.
Sprinkle cheese and optional jalapenos over top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.
Ole!

title: bryan's beef jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cut roast into strips and marinate over night.
Dehydrate for 6-9 hours depending on thickness of jerky.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix syrup and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute. Add peanut butter and butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Add cornflakes and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or covered cookie sheet.
Serves 36.

title: reuben's
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve on miniature rye bread.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken pieces on bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine; mix well.
Spoon this sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over the mixture.
Drizzle with the melted butter.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Pound steak. Cut into bite size pieces. In skillet, brown steak in shortening. Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients. Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: blueberry cheesecake(a taste treat from linda)
directions: Mix and put into a pie plate.
Bake for 5 minutes at 375°.

title: coconut pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix ingredients, then bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. This pie needs no crust; it makes its own.

title: tuna mold
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Pour 1 cup cold water over 2 envelopes unflavored gelatin in a medium saucepan.
Heat until gelatin is dissolved.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise until desired moistness. Good on crackers, as sandwich filling, to fill small cream puffs, pocket or pita bread.

title: punch for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve over ice.

title: chutney cheese ball
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Shape cheese mixture into a ball; roll in chopped nuts.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Yields one 5-inch ball.

title: chocolate oat cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Bring to boil (full boil) for 1 minute.
Take off and add vanilla flavoring and oats.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper and let harden.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients in order. Make hole in bread. Tear pieces of the pulled out center into finger size pieces and lay around bread bowl. Fill bread bowl with dip.

title: quick potato salad
directions: Cut slightly cooled potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, onions and salad dressing, then toss gently.
Dust with paprika or black pepper.
Garnish with chives and bacon.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm. Makes a good luncheon dish.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix together all ingredients, pour in freezer and finish filling with regular milk.

title: sausage and peppers with rice
directions: In large skillet, cook sausage, onion and green pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain off all grease.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with garlic powder.
Marinate, shaking to coat, with oil for 2 hours or overnight.
Drain.
Mix together crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Coat chicken with crumb mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook onion in melted butter about 10 minutes.
Add celery, salt and pepper.
Add chicken stock; cover and cook 10 minutes. Add drained vegetables, water chestnuts and diced chicken; mix well and heat to boiling.
Add sauce.

title: italian bread sticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2/3 cup warm water; add salt, sugar and shortening.
Beat in 1 cup flour until smooth.
Knead in remaining flour for 5 minutes.
Shape into 20 (6-inch) pencil lengths.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Beat egg and remaining water together.
Brush on sticks.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake for 20 minutes at 370°.
Yields 20.

title: lemon cheese filling
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt. Add beaten egg, water, lemon juice and rind. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear. Add oleo and the food coloring.
Will ice 2 layers of plain cake.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Whip egg whites. Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, and continue to whip until egg whites form peaks. Scald milk and add to egg whites while beating. Add butter or oleo, 1 teaspoon at a time. Then add shortening and vanilla. Beat for a long time until desired consistency.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; press into a 9-inch pie plate. Do not bake.

title: clam stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplants in half lengthwise.
Place cut side down in shallow baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Scoop out eggplant; leave 1/2-inch shell.
Chop eggplant; saute with celery, onion and garlic in 1/4 cup oil about 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Spoon into shells.
Brush outside rims and top with oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grampy's fudge
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large saucepan.
Stir over low heat until blended.
Bring to boil over mod heat, being careful not to mistake air bubbles for boiling.
Then boil slowly, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat stir in chocolate chips and vanilla until chocolate is melted.
Pour into 2 buttered 9 x 9 inch pans and cool.
Makes 5 lb.
Store at room temp.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Coat casserole dish with Pam.
Place broccoli in dish.
Mix last 5 ingredients.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with fine bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 10 inch greased skillet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian orange delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Blend in frozen orange juice. Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in crushed pineapple and Mandarin oranges.
Fold in miniature marshmallows and coconut.
Chill until firm.

title: candied pecans
directions: Cook until dry.
Then place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes on 350 degrees.
Don't let burn.
Take off cookie sheet.
Store in dry container.

title: lo-cal banana split cake
directions: Place graham crackers in an 8-inch square pan.
Mix pudding and milk and pur over graham crackers.
Slice banana and layer over pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over the bananas.
Top with strawberries and pineapple.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cover and chill macaroni.
Combine remaining ingredients and chill.
Combine all ingredients just before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Bake pie shells for 5 minutes; let cool.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 16 to 18.

title: cauliflower and lettuce salad
directions: Break up lettuce and place in medium size bowl.
Place broken cauliflower over lettuce.
Fry bacon.
Let cool and crumble mix with chopped green pepper.
Place on top of cauliflower.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice, green pepper and onion in oil in large skillet. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Do not stir or uncover for best results.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Heat oil in a wok or pan and stir-fry celery and onion over high heat for 2 to 3 minutes, separating the onion "layers."
Add soy sauce, sugar and broth; bring to a boil.
Add bean sprouts and chicken and stir to combine.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add gradually to sauce.
Simmer gently until it thickens.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Serves 4.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix and pour over the crust.
Top with Cool Whip and 1 more crumbled Butterfinger.
Chill.

title: picadillo
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Add tomato sauce, basil and oregano.
Cook until boiling; add raisins.
Simmer on medium-low heat for about 30 minutes.
Prepare yellow rice as directed on package.
Serve with fried plantains or sliced bananas.

title: brandy alexander
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in blender.
Pour into champagne glasses and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: midnight mix
directions: Place the cereal and pecans in a pan and place aside; pour butter and cheese over cereal.
Bake at 200° and stir often.

title: mints
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth and creamy.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Place on waxed paper.
Flatten with palm of your hands.
Let dry 10 to 15 minutes, then use tines of fork to flatten (making a crisscross pattern).
When tops feel dry, turn mints over to dry.
Store in airtight container between layers of waxed paper in refrigerator.

title: crunchy cheese potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream, milk, chives, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Spread in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking dish.
Combine cheese and cornflakes; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with additional chives, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana cherry salad
directions: In large flat pan, smush bananas into small pieces.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Freeze.
Serve frozen or may thaw for 30 minutes prior to eating.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well; pour into greased and floured 9 or 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Pour chicken broth into 4-quart pot.
Put in chicken tenders. Cook about 10 minutes.
Remove. Cut into pieces.
Return to chicken broth.
Add diced tomatoes and mixed vegetables.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift and mix thoroughly the first 5 ingredients in 10 x 6-inch (8 x 8-inch would also work) cake pan.
Make 3 holes in above mixture.
Put vinegar in one hole, vanilla in another hole and oil in third hole.
Pour cold water over all and mix with fork until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Can add chopped nuts.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a doubled plastic food bag. Shake well.
Spray Pam or use oil to prepare an 10 x 15 x 3-inch pan.
Use cold water to wash chicken and then paper towel dry.
Add chicken to bag, a few pieces at a time, and shake.
Continue until all chicken is used up.
Melt butter and using a soft pastry brush, dab each piece of chicken, until all are covered.
Bake them, uncovered, without turning.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coreene's spiced tea mix
directions: Mix ingredients and keep in tightly covered jar.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup of hot water.
Great on cold wet days!

title: grandma o'dell's french crullers
directions: Heat the water to a boil.
Add the butter and when melted stir the flour in quickly.
Remove from fire and cool slightly.
Add eggs, not beaten, one at a time and mix thoroughly.
Shape the crullers on an oiled brown bag, using bag.
Fry in deep fat at 395° until golden brown.
Drain and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: never fail pastry
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse meal. Stir in remaining ingredients. (Work like kneading bread dough.) Divide dough into 5 balls. Wrap tightly in plastic wrap and store in freezer bags.
May be stored up to 5 weeks in freezer. Yields 5 (9-inch) pies.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill for several hours or overnight.

title: oyster cracker appetizers
directions: Mix crackers and oil together.
Add dry ingredients and mix again.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir.
May be stored at room temperature, in covered container.

title: date bars
directions: Grease and flour 7 1/2 x 12-inch pan.
Mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: gene's meat loaf gravy
directions: Heat oil and flour in large skillet until light brown.
Add all other items.
Only takes about 5 minutes.
If gravy gets too thick, add more water.
Serve over meat loaf.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium high heat.
Add chicken, onions and peppers.
Cook and stir until cheese is cooked through. Add corn and salsa, bring to a boil.
You may add a little water, if needed.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover.
Let stand 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour a 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, tomato juice, oats, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix all together in a bowl.

title: doughnut drops
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoon into hot oil (370° for electric frypan).
Drain on paper towel.
Coat with cinnamon and sugar or powdered sugar.

title: fried rice(a great main dish)
directions: Fry bacon pieces.
Remove bacon and saute onion, green onion and carrot.
Leave crisp.
Add meat, peas, salt and pepper.
In a separate pan, cook 2 scrambled eggs.
Chop eggs and add to meat mixture.
Add cooked rice to meat mixture and stir.
Add 1/4 c. soy sauce and stir until ready to serve.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring, until smooth.
Cook one minute.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add cheese.
Stir in salt and pepper.

title: pull away bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in small bowl.
Stir boiling water and shortening and dissolve in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Cover bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Knead.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted butter.
Line around the bottom and up the sides of a Bundt cake pan.
Fill pan up around the stem of pan, too.
Let rise 1 hour (covered).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine lemon juice, salt and mayonnaise. Stir into cream cheese.
Add pineapple, cherries and nuts. Fold in whipped cream. Add bananas.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Yields 10 servings.

title: smothered steak casserole
directions: Season and flour steak. Brown in fat.
Arrange in bottom of casserole. Cover with raw potatoes and carrots. Pour soup
and milk over vegetables and meat. Cover and bake 35 minutes at 400°. Remove cover.
Place biscuits over top.
Return to oven and bake about 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beans and rice
directions: In a nonstick skillet, saute onion and garlic in oil until tender. Stir in the tomatoes, zucchini and oregano. Cover and cook for 5 to 6 minutes, until zucchini is tender, stirring occasionally. Add the beans, salt and pepper; cook and stir until heated through. Serve over cooked rice, sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Place fruit in clear glass bowl.
Coat with lemon and orange juice. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Bake pie shell 8 minutes.
Beat egg whites.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until soft peaks.
Beat remaining ingredients and yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: squash muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, squash in large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil; add to dry mixture, stirring until moistened.
Spoon batter into lightly greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Freeze well.

title: deluxe potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle a little sugar over fruit and mix with one cup or one carton of sour cream.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In a large soup kettle or Dutch oven, melt the butter.
Stir in flour; heat and stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add potatoes and onions. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until cheese
is melted.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings (2 1/2 quarts).

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Remove chicken from bone.
In a casserole layer noodles, chicken, onion, bell pepper, and cheese.
Mix cream of chicken soup with chicken broth.
Heat and pour over each layer.
Make 3 layers. Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.
Serves 4-6.

title: chestnut cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and nuts together.
Pour into a buttered Pyrex dish.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, sugar, eggs and melted butter completely.
Mix together.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: backpack cookies
directions: Cream butter in a large bowl; gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Fold in oats and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.
Transfer cookies to wire racks and let cool completely.
Yield:
7 1/2 dozen.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Knead together all ingredients.
Heat oven to 350°.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Set balls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Eat warm. These can be warmed for leftovers or eaten when you need a quick breakfast.

title: best buttermilk rolls
directions: Combine yeast, 1/4 cup lukewarm water and 1 tablespoon sugar in a large bowl.
Stir until yeast is dissolved.
Set aside.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Combine chicken pieces and lemon pieces in a bowl just large enough to hold them comfortably.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator overnight, turning occasionally.

title: orange roughy
directions: Cover fish
in
Italian dressing and let marinate for 3 to 4 hours.
Take
out of marinade and wrap in heavy aluminum foil. Place
on
the
grill and cook five minutes.
Turn over and cook another five.
Pierce the foil some for the last five minutes
to give them the grilled taste.
Additional marinade may be used to baste during cooking if you choose.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Roll 1 teaspoon
dough in balls, dip in slightly beaten egg white, then in nuts.
Place
on
pan.
Press
thumb gently into centers.
Bake 10 to
20 minutes.
Fill holes with jelly. Strawberry jam is best.

title: cabbage and dumplings
directions: Mix together and either roll or drop.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package.
Bake in 9X13 pan and allow to completely cool.
Using a fork, prick holes all over pan of brownies.
Drizzle with coffee liqueur.
Break up brownies into small pieces; place half in bottom of large glass bowl or truffle dish.
Cover with half pudding, 1/3 of crushed candy and half the Cool Whip.
Repeat with another layer.
Top with remaining third of crushed candy.
Cover and chill for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Drain off liquid.
Add soup, milk, broccoli and chicken.
Add seasoning from Ramen noodles to taste.
Serves 2.

title: mexicali pork chops
directions: Rub taco seasoning over pork chops.
In a skillet, cook chops in oil over medium-high heat until meat is no longer pink and juices run clear, about 9 minutes.	Serve with salsa.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: grandma's applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, eggs and applesauce.
Rub raisins with flour.
Add with all remaining ingredients to creamed mixture. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or two loaf pans about 1 hour at 325°.

title: toni's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat sugars and butter in a large bowl until fluffy.
Beat in Bristol Cream and eggs.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop dough about 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 11 to 14 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.

title: sour cream coconut icing
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours before using.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chickens; remove meat; cut into chunks.
In a greased casserole, combine the chicken, mayonnaise, celery, almonds, cream of chicken soup, onion, lemon juice, Tabasco, salt and pepper. Toss to mix and cook at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Put potato chips on top to serve.

title: pork chops with apples
directions: Brown pork chops and onion in a large skillet coated with cooking spray. Combine water, bouillon granules, and pepper, stirring to dissolve; add to skillet. Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes. Skim off fat. Add apple slices and cinnamon mixture in skillet. Cove and simmer an additional 15 minutes. Transfer to a serving platter, and serve hot. Yield 4 servings.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter. Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition just until yellow disappears. Add flour alternately with cream, beginning and ending with flour. Stir in vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Cool in pan on rack about 10 minutes. Cool completely on rack.

title: carolyn sue's hot crab dip
directions: Chop crab meat fine.
Mix all with crab.
Heat in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers or chips.

title: texas melt
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add enchilada sauce, stewed tomatoes, onions, salt and pepper; bring to a boil and simmer. Spread sour cream on tortillas and fold in half.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spread enough sauce to cover bottom of pan.
Place tortillas on top of meat mixture (sauce) and pour remaining sauce over tortillas.
Top with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: "civil war" or date loaf bread
directions: Combine dates, water, soda, salt and butter and let cool and then add beaten egg, sugar, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well and bake 1 hour at 350° or until done in center.

title: caramel cake
directions: Unwrap caramels and put in saucepan with 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Heat until melted, stirring constantly; set aside.

title: microwave fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts in egg whites, then roll chicken breasts in crushed corn flakes.
Arrange in microwave dish.
Cover with Saran Wrap except for one corner.
Cook in microwave for 20 minutes.
Microwaves vary so check to see if chicken is done.
You may have to add some time.
Turn dish every 5 minutes during cooking.

title: rosie's mexican dip
directions: Layer in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or microwave until cheese is melted.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch lined pie plate.
Pour 1 cup heavy cream over berries.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Dilute frozen juices with 2 cans water for each can.
Dissolve sugar in 1 cup boiling water; let cool.
Add sweetened water and jello to juices.
Add ginger ale and mashed bananas, 2 hours before serving.

title: fireside coffee mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.
To make 1 cup, spoon 2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon coffee mix in cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water.

title: eclaire
directions: Prepare pudding, fold in cook whip.
Layer graham crackers and pudding mix in 9 x 13 pan starting with graham crackers.
To with chocolate sauce.
Cool for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: fish and chips
directions: Mix first three ingredients until the consistency of buttermilk.
Then dip fish in flour and let dry a few minutes. Then dip in batter.

title: broccoli-cheddar soup(low-cal)
directions: Cut and discard the hardest part of the stalk.
Separate broccoli into flowerets and stalks. Dice stalks and chop flowerets.
Put broccoli in boiling water and cook about 8 minutes. Drain and set aside.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, heat the oil over moderately high heat until very hot but not smoking.
Add onions, red peppers, garlic and celery.
Saute for 7 minutes, until onions are golden. Stir in the chili powder, cumin, jalapeno pepper, salt, carrots, mushrooms, water and tomatoes.
Bring the liquid to a boil over high heat; then lower the heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until carrots are barely tender.
Add the beans and cover. Cook for 5 minutes or until they are heated through.
Uncover saucepan; continue to cook for 10 minutes or until the liquid has thickened slightly.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetable, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp
directions: Marinate shrimp in French dressing in fridge for 1-2 hours. Dressing need not cover shrimp but turn once and then drain shrimp.
Wrap each shrimp in 1/4 piece of bacon.
Secure bacon with tooth pick.
Place on oven rack in a shallow pan and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until bacon is dry or crisp.
Do not over cook shrimp.
Drain on a paper towel and enjoy!

title: french toast
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and sugar. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in 10-inch frypan.
Dip bread, one slice at a time, in egg mixture.
Then fry in oil over low heat.
When brown on one side, turn and brown other side.
When done, sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Serve with syrup or jelly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except barbecue sauce.
Spread mixture evenly in loaf dish (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Spread barbecue sauce over meat mixture.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 12 minutes.
Rotate loaf dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave until center is no longer pink, 13 to 16 minutes longer.
Remove to serving platter; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Top with additional sauce if desired.

title: angel hair primavera
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil; set aside.
Steam broccoli; set aside.
Cook peas; set aside.
Toss pasta with garlic oil, peas, broccoli and tomatoes.
Serve immediately.

title: sausage-cheese meat balls
directions: Mix all together; form into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook until hot and bubbly; 2 to 3 hours on high in crock-pot or 1 hour at 350°.

title: baklava
directions: Grind almonds and walnuts and add sugar and cinnamon.
Butter pan and add five phyllo, buttering each layer.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil the sugar and water and cool.
Blend all together. Put in container and freeze.
Let thaw some before serving and stir well.

title: sausage alfresco
directions: Prepare fettucine, drain.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion, then vegetables; cook until tender.
Set aside; brown sausage and drain.
Combine sausage, vegetables and cream.
Simmer; add cheese and parsley.
Serve over fettucine.

title: sharon's favorite bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mixture should be very moist, but not soupy.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch or larger baking dish. Place into non-preheated oven.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes until top is golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: elephant ears
directions: Cut tortillas in half and deep fry until crisp (about 1 minute on each side).
Drain well and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Cream milk, margarine, vanilla, pecans and coconut.
Add sugar; mix well.
Roll in small balls and chill about 1 hour. Put a toothpick in each ball.
In top of double boiler, melt chocolate and paraffin.
Dip chilled balls in hot chocolate and put on wax paper.
Remove toothpick.
Keep chocolate hot while coating.
Do not try to double recipe.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Dissolve vinegar, sugar and salt.
Mix first 5 ingredients. Mix the 2 mixtures together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
This keeps for 2 weeks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in regular order.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Sprinkle with Morton Nature's Seasons.
Place chicken in a baking dish or pan.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb and jello preserves
directions: Cover rhubarb with sugar and let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Cook sauce.
Take off from fire and add Jell-O.
Blend well and pour into sterilized jars or jelly glasses.

title: sausage strata
directions: Fit bread into bottom of a greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish. Brown, then drain, the sausage well.
Stir in the mustard.
Spoon sausage evenly over the bread, then sprinkle with cheese.

title: aunt mim's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients first.
Batter will be tacky.
Roll out dough thin and cut out your designs.
Try not to use extra flour.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.

title: brownie pie
