directions: Mix sugar and melted butter. Add beaten eggs. Combine cocoa, salt and flour. Add to sugar, butter and eggs. Add vanilla. Grease and flour 8-inch pie pan and pour in batter. Cook at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve with ice cream.

title: honey thyme vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package; drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into hot vegetables.
Makes 5 servings.

title: patio cooler
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan and place over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Combine with tea and fruit juices.
Chill several hours.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale and pour over ice.
Can be used in punch bowl with ice ring. Makes 3 quarts.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cover peaches with water and bring to a boil.
Add sugar to canned peaches.

title: taco salad
directions: Shred lettuce.
Cut up tomato; drain and rinse kidney beans. Drain garbanzo beans.
Slice onion, crumble chips.
Mix preceding ingredients (reserving half of crumbled chips to sprinkle on top). Add dressing and toss.
Sprinkle chips on top.

title: cheese popovers
directions: Sift flour and salt into a bowl.
Beat eggs and milk together, then add to the flour, beating until quite smooth.
Add a few drops of Tabasco.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, margarine and milk until well blended.
Stir in bread and pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Add flour, sifted with soda.
Add vanilla.
Add nuts last.
Drop from spoon on
greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 14 minutes.

title: pumpkin-raisin loaves
directions: In mixing bowl, combine the pumpkin, water, egg and spice. Add the muffin mix and raisins.
Stir until moistened.

title: chicken or turkey hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set the pan in a larger pan of water and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: coffee can batter bread
directions: This recipe may be baked in one 2 pound coffee can or two 1 pound coffee cans.
Grease both can and lid.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Mix everything except chocolate by hand until smooth and pliable.
Chill.
Roll into balls and chill until firm.
Dip balls into melted chocolate; place on waxed paper until firm and set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice separately according to instructions on package.
Combine all ingredients into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken yum-yum
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Roll in flour.
Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish in a 350° oven.
Place floured chicken in Pyrex dish.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, turning chicken after 15 minutes.
Mix soup with 1 can of water and pour over chicken. Cover and cook 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 1 or 2 loaf pans (greased) at 350° for 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and oil until light and fluffy; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to other creamed ingredients.
Blend well.
Chill dough about 1 hour.
Roll into small balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.
Loosen cookies before they cool and stick to cookie sheet.

title: macaroni and vegetable medley
directions: Drain macaroni; add soup, milk and cream cheese.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower until tender; drain.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Put margarine in a deep pan. Set in 350° oven to melt.
Stir batter of remaining sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Place peaches on top.
Bake for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.
Batter rises to the top during baking.

title: chocolate peanut butter chip fudge
directions: Combine cream, sweetened condensed milk and chocolate syrup. Beat with an electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Transfer to a 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; freeze until firm.
Makes 1 quart; 8 servings.

title: creamy vegetable dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, mayonnaise and anchovy paste. Stir in chopped egg, parsley, onion and garlic.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with vegetables.
Makes 1 3/4 cups dip.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Boil noodles.
Layer 13 x 9-inch pan, starting with sauce, noodles, sauce, cheeses (Mozzarella cheese, use a little or a lot).
Layer until pan is full.
Top should just be sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese is melted down.

title: party potatoes
directions: Wash, peel, slice and cook potatoes until soft.
Turn into an electric mixer bowl and add sour cream, cream cheese and butter or margarine.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: sherry pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Beat in sugar.
Combine with pumpkin, cream, spices and salt.
Cook over a very low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens or cook in a double boiler.
Soften gelatin in sherry; dissolve in hot pumpkin mixture.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Chill until mixture thickens.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry; fold into filling.
Mound in baked pastry shell.
Chill until firm.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Combine all of the 7 ingredients, then separately mix 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 teaspoon of lemon juice and add to chicken mixture.
Then sprinkle crushed potato chips on top and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: daisy's casserole
directions: Saute beef and onion; add water chestnuts, mushrooms, tomatoes, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Add to beef mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cracklin' cornbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Add buttermilk, stirring until well mixed. Add cracklins and pour into a very hot iron skillet which has been well-greased. Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter, vanilla extract, milk and pumpkin (either fresh or canned). Use whisk or fork to stir well.
Pour into pie crust. Bake in regular pie crust. Makes 2 pies. Preheat oven to 400° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: An angel food cake baked from scratch is so much better for this recipe.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Saute chops on both sides.
Place chops in buttered casserole. Place 1 tablespoon raw rice on each chop, 1 slice onion and 1 slice tomato.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 1/2 cups water; pour over all.
Sprinkle with herbs, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes; cover and simmer.

title: kringla
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add egg and beat. Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with the buttermilk.
Chill for 2 hours or longer.
Form figure eights and bake in 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick cheese ball
directions: Fold cream cheese, onions and 1 package of ham together; mix in Accent.
Form into a ball and cover with remaining package of ham (cut into squares or chopped fine).
Refrigerate until set.

title: green enchiladas casserole
directions: In skillet brown hamburger and onion.
Set aside.
In a saucepan heat remaining ingredients, except corn chips, until cheese is melted.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish alternately layer meat, corn chips and cheese sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and lima bean salad
directions: Cook lima beans according to package.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
In a mixing bowl, combine beans, mushrooms, onion, bacon, olives, parsley and pimiento.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add pizza sauce and simmer.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook noodles until done. In 12-inch square casserole dish, layer noodles, ground beef and sauce mixture and Cheddar cheese.
Top with pepperoni and mushrooms.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on this layer.
Garnish with green onions.
Bake in microwave until cheese melts and dish has heated through, approximately 10 minutes or bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pineapple mint jelly
directions: Cover the mint with 1/2 cup water and 2 tablespoons sugar in with mint.
Let stand overnight.
Strain into pot, then add pineapple juice, lemon juice and 4 cups sugar.
Bring to boil; add 1/2 cup liquid pectin.
Boil 1/2 minute.
Add green coloring. Skim and pour into jelly glasses.
Makes about 6 (6 ounce) jars.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Stir 1/2 lb caramels and 2 tbsp hot water over hot water until smooth. Pour over 5 c popped corn, kix or cheerios. Mix gently until blended. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: patio punch
directions: Combine drink powders and sugar. Add water and stir to dissolve. Add frozen concentrate. Chill until serving time. Pour over ice. Pour gingerale slowly down side of bowl. Makes about 4 qts.

title: bunny's fried rice
directions: Saute green
onions
in olive
oil.
Cook 1 cup rice in 2 1/2 cups of water.
Add cooked rice, soy sauce and sugar to green onions.
Heat through.
Add boiled ham.
Then add softly scrambled eggs and heat quickly.

title: baked tomato and spinach
directions: Melt butter and saute onions and garlic, add spinach.
Remove from heat in breadcrumbs, egg and salt.
Put into halves of tomato and put into a baking dish.
Refrigerate a couple of hours.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: french-toasted ham and cheese
directions: In cup, stir marmalade and mustard until mixed.
Set aside. Cut ham slices to fit on half of the bread slice; cut cheese slices to fit on top of ham, then top with a dollop of marmalade mixture and another bread slice.
Preheat oven to 450°.
In 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jellyroll pan, melt butter; remove pan from oven. In pie plate with fork, beat milk and egg until mixed.
Dip sandwiches, one at a time, into egg mixture to coat all sides. Place sandwiches in one layer in jellyroll pan.
Bake until sandwiches are golden brown on both sides, or about 20 minutes, turning once.
Cut each sandwich in half.
Serve hot.

title: ruthie's drop molasses cookies
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pepper steak
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Add garlic and brown in oil.
Cook until garlic is yellow.
Add soy sauce and water.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes (no more than 30).
Add vegetables except tomatoes and cook, covered, about 15 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Stir into skillet mixture.
Add tomatoes.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: farmhouse chowder
directions: Simmer potatoes and onions in broth until tender, about 10 minutes.
In separate pan, cook butter and flour until bubbly. Add milk and water to butter and flour mixture.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Add this mixture to the potatoes, onions and broth. Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Add cheese and eggs just before serving.
Be sure to add all liquids from can of vegetables.

title: twenty minute tamale pie
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet with cover.
Add onion and meat and cook until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, corn with liquid, sour cream, corn meal, olives and seasonings.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes its own crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: summer fruit pie
directions: Cook all fruit (except blueberries) on top of stove with the sugar and juice.
Cook until a light boil.
Remove from heat; add cornstarch, butter and blueberries.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Bake in oven until bubbly.
You may need to heat cheese in microwave before mixing ingredients.

title: wet chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Batter will be thin. Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mixing well over low heat and bring to a boil for 1/2 to 1 minute (no more or less).
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add oats and stir quickly.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Cook onion, garlic and peppers in hot oil for about 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook 3 or 4 minutes.
(I often use a can of pasta-style chunky tomatoes, undrained.) Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in beans and cover and let simmer while rice is cooking.
Serve over rice.

title: hawaiian kabobs
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup of juice.
In large bowl, place pineapple chunks and vegetables.
Set aside.
In a saucepan, combine pineapple juice with soy sauce, olive oil, brown sugar and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Pour over vegetable mixture; cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Heat honey, cider vinegar, onion and mustard in saucepan.
Add oil; heat for 5 minutes.
Toss spinach with dressing just before serving and garnish with all remaining ingredients.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add cheese to meat and melt. Add chili and sour cream.
Serve in layers.
Crumble chips; put hamburger mixture, then tomatoes, lettuce and salsa.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and arrange pineapple rings.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: snowball cookies(shortbread nuggets)
directions: Cream sugar and softened margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mixture will be lumpy.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Form teaspoonfuls of mixture into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned on the bottom.
While still warm, roll in sifted confectioners sugar.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain peas and chill.
Boil eggs and chill.
Add onion, pickles, salt, pepper and mayonnaise to peas; chill.
Serve cold.

title: chili
directions: Cook and stir ground beef until browned; drain excess fat. Stir in onions and peppers and cook until onions are clear (tender).
Stir in remaining ingredients except Tabasco and corn meal.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat and simmer (covered) for two hours, stirring occasionally.
Mix corn meal with small amount of water to dissolve and use it to thicken chili, as desired. Taste chili and use Tabasco for smooth, mellow, hot flavor.

title: beef roast with mushrooms
directions: In large, heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Peel onion and stick cloves into onion.
Add onion, mushrooms and salt and pepper.
Cover tightly and simmer for 30 minutes per pound.
Check occasionally for moisture.
Add a little wine or water if needed.
When roast is tender, meat juice may be thickened with sour cream or thinned with wine.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Combine 1/4 cup corn syrup, brown sugar and butter in medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal, stirring until well coated.
Press in 9-inch pie pan to form crust.
Stir together peanut butter, fudge sauce and the 3 tablespoons corn syrup.
Spread half the peanut butter mixture over crust.
Freeze until firm.
Allow ice cream to soften.
Spoon into frozen pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Let pie stand at room temperature before cutting.
Sprinkle over few chopped peanuts, then warm remaining peanut butter mixture and drizzle over top.

title: bates meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Form in balls.
Bake in jelly roll pan in oven for 15 minutes at 350° or until done.
Place in sauce (recipe follows) and return to oven to hold warm.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll out on pizza pan.
Be sure to go up the sides.
Brown the sausage.
Drain well.
Mix in hash browns. Spread on dough.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix eggs with milk. Pour over everything.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook ground beef and onions over medium heat until browned. Add next 8 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add vegetables, noodles and thyme.
Bring to a boil and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.

title: sweet treat
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour applesauce in pan.
Pour crushed pineapple into pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over applesauce/pineapple mixture.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Put nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Eat with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add onion; set aside. Microwave Velveeta cheese and salsa in 1 1/2-quart bowl on High for 5 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, then add ground beef. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) plastic cups.

title: sloppy joes turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet sprayed with cooking spray, brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Add tomato sauce, salt, brown sugar substitute and garlic powder.
Simmer 5 minutes. Separate crescent roll dough into triangles.
Lay triangles on large ungreased cookie sheet.
Place about 1 tablespoon of meat mixture in center of each triangle.
Bring 3 corners together in center of each triangle.
Bake for 12 to 16 minutes or until golden brown.
Each serving is 2 triangles.

title: mama's hot potato salad
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add margarine and chopped eggs to hot potatoes.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve hot.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread coconut on bottom of 11 x 15 x 2-inch pan (do not use any smaller size pan).
Cover coconut with pecans.
Prepare cake
mix	as
directed
on box and pour over pecans and	coconut.
Mix
cream
cheese, oleo, sugar and vanilla. Drop by spoonful
over cake mix.
Do not stir.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp appetizers
directions: Wrap bacon strips around each shrimp and secure with toothpick. Dip in chili sauce seasoned with Tabasco sauce.
Grill, turning until brown and bacon is crisp and lightly browned.
Serve hot; 3 to 4 per serving.

title: pimento dip
directions: Put everything in medium bowl and beat well. 1-2 minutes. Best if made 24 hours ahead. Serve with Scoops.

title: upside-down berry cake
directions: Place first sugar and butter in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 3 to 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and mix, spreading evenly. Mix together berries, 1/2 cup sugar and flour.
Pour over butter mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients until moist.
Pour over berries, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Run knife around edge to loosen cake.
Turn upside down on serving tray.
Serve warm or cold.

title: golden puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well with fork.
Heat oil or Crisco 2 inches deep in deep-fat fryer or a kettle.
Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown on both sides, about 3 minutes.
Remove to paper towels to drain.
May be rolled in sugar.
To make a fruit puff add 1/2 cup shredded
apple to the batter.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: quick veggie soup
directions: In large pot, add tomato juice and chicken broth.
Add all veggies.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: chocolate caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: no-cook divinity
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water.
Beat on highest speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to large mixer bowl.
On low speed, gradually blend in sugar.
Stir in nuts.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except pastry shell.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until center is set.
Cool.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: corn souffle elegante
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, mushrooms, onion and corn and pour into a well-greased souffle dish.
Beat eggs, half and half and parsley together and pour over the top.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: venison with sour cream and mushrooms
directions: Season meat with marjoram, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in 1/4 cup flour.
Heat shortening in
a large skillet.
Brown meat quickly on both sides.
Remove.
Reduce heat.
Saute onions and mushrooms until onions are tender.
Add sherry, bouillon cube and water and stir well.
Return meat to gravy and continue cooking until meat is medium rate.
Combine sour cream and flour.
Stir into pan and heat, stirring until gravy thickens (add more sherry if too thick).
Do not let gravy boil.
Serves 4.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mix all ingredients. Pour into casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick butter, add crushed Ritz crackers (approximately 20) and spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Stir soups, sour cream and green chilies until it bubbles. Fill tortillas with cheese and onion.
Cover rolled tortillas with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frijoles rancheros beans
directions: Wash and soak beans for 45 minutes.
Cook beans for about 1 hour and 35 minutes.
Before beans are ready, fry the strips of bacon until crisp, then in the same bacon pan, add salt and onions and the small jalapeno.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add the tomato sauce; cook for another 5 minutes.
When beans are soft and done, pour the mixture of the pan into the beans.
Cook for 5 minutes. It should be mixed thoroughly.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
In 10-inch skillet, brown in hot shortening.
Pour off drippings.
Mix cream of chicken soup, Pet milk and water.
Pour around pork chops.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Stir gravy well.

title: cinnamon puffs
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Add margarine, shortening and egg yolk.
Mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in 2/3 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon, combined.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Use an 8-inch glass pie plate.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. It makes its own crust!

title: nutty blue cheese rolls
directions: For filling, in a medium bowl, stir together walnuts, Blue cheese, 1 tablespoon parsley and pepper.

title: microwave potato au gratin
directions: Combine potatoes, soup, sour cream and 1/2 cup of the cheese in 1 3/4-quart shallow microproof casserole; blend well.
Cook on High 10 to 11 minutes, or until potatoes are tender, stirring once during cooking time.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese. Cover and let stand 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: three way chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add flour to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating until smooth after each addition.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, spread with chocolate frosting.

title: party potato salad
directions: Dice and boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix with cooled potatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jimmy's favorite pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Make pretzel shapes with dough (can make numbers for birthdays or holidays).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten whole egg.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 5 minutes.
Turn over and bake 5 more minutes or until your choice of brown/crispness.

title: greek lemon soup
directions: Into large saucepan, dissolve bouillon in water; add rice. Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
In small bowl, beat eggs and lemon juice.
Gradually stir about 1/2 cup hot bouillon mixture into eggs; stir into hot soup.
Serve immediately.

title: p-nut krispies
directions: Mix together sugar and Karo syrup and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Blend well and add Cocoa Krispies.
Blend well and drop on wax paper by teaspoonfuls.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and baking powder.
Blend with egg mixture.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Place in pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chuckwagon casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients but last 3. Use 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Dip biscuits in butter, then in corn meal. Arrange on top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken yakitori
directions: In saucepan over low heat, stir brown sugar, soy sauce, cold water, 3 tablespoons oil and the mustard until dissolved.
Cool mixture.
Pour over chicken in bowl and marinate at room temperature 2 hours (or overnight in refrigerator).
Place vegetable at center of broiler pan.
Top with rack; brush with oil.
Add chicken; brush with oil.
Cook for 20 minutes, turning once and basting often.
Combine rice and hot water in pan. Drizzle with some of the marinade.
Place by the chicken and cook about 15 minutes, turning chicken and stirring rice occasionally. Chicken will be quite dark.
Serve on platter with almonds and parsley sprinkled on rice.
Serves 4.

title: fondue neuchateloise(this is a traditional fondue)
directions: Rub cooking pot with cut garlic.
Add wine and heat.
When wine is hot, but not boiling, add lemon juice.
Add cheese by handfuls, stirring constantly with wooden spoon until cheese is smooth and melted.
Bring fondue to bubble briefly.
Add seasonings, stirring until blended.
Mix cornstarch with Kirsch liqueur.
Add to fondue; allow to boil for another 30 seconds. Serve and keep hot over burner.
Spear bread cubes through soft side into crust; dunk and swirl in fondue.

title: corn bread salad(to eat with soup beans.)
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
It is better the second day after preparation.

title: blueberry orange muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Combine dry ingredients.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: my chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
When cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: fruited blue cheese dressing
directions: In tightly covered jar, shake Blue cheese dressing, orange juice and lemon juice together.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours to blend flavors.
Shake well.

title: stroganoff stew
directions: Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper over meat.
In large stockpot, heat oil.
Add meat; cook until browned.
Add beef broth and water.
Add the rest of the ingredients except sour cream.
Boil, then reduce heat to medium low and simmer 50 to 55 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.

title: pecan snack
directions: Put pecans and slightly beaten egg whites in a bowl and stir. Sprinkle in sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Spread and separate on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook until sugar dissolves.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
(If using Pyrex baking dish, bake at 425° for 30 minutes.)

title: apple-cranberry wild rice
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water and salt to a boil. Stir in the rice; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until rice is tender. Drain.

Stir in savory; set aside. In a nonstick skillet, saute leek in oil for 1 minute. Stir in cranberries, apples and 3 tablespoons chicken broth; cover and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add rice, onion salt, lemon pepper and remaining broth. Cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Yield: 6 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
In bowl, combine hamburger with sour cream, soup, drained pimentos and drained corn.
Fold in cooked (drained) noodles.
Top with 2 cups Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Prepare devil's food cake mix as directed.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Cream for 15 minutes the margarine, shortening, sugar and flour.
To this add vanilla and milk.
Spread on cooled cake; refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.

title: it's-a-snap cheesecake
directions: In a small saucepan sprinkle gelatine over 1/4 cup cold water. Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved.
In a large bowl with electric mixer, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until blended.
Gradually beat in gelatine mixture and remaining 3/4 cup water until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Chill until firm.
Garnish, if desired, with fresh or canned fruit.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour in Bundt pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Dust with powdered sugar or make drizzle icing with powdered sugar and water.

title: old virginia spoon bread
directions: Stir
cornmeal	and
salt
into 2 cups boiling water in saucepan.
Cook
for
minute; remove from heat.	Add melted butter and baking powder; mix well.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in milk
gradually.
Spoon into 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: york brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; stir in flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend well.
Reserve 2 cups batter; set aside. Spread remaining batter in pan.
Arrange patties in single layer over batter about 1/2 inch apart.
Spread reserved batter over patties.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Yield:
About 36 brownies.

title: pineapple meringue pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour with a pastry blender until it's a crumb mixture.
Stir in cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time, to form a dough ball.
Roll out dough on a floured surface to fit an 8-inch pie pan.
Place dough in pie pan, trim and decorate edge and bake at 475° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Put ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover.
Cook on high for 1 hour and then on low for 4 to 8 hours.
Serve hot.

title: corn pudding
directions: Bake in buttered dish slowly for at least 1 hour.

title: marvelous mocha cheesecake
directions: In small bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and margarine or butter. Pat crumbs firmly in 9 x 13-inch baking pan (on bottom and sides of dish).
Chill.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Add Eagle Brand and chocolate syrup.
In small bowl, dissolve coffee in water.
Add to Eagle Brand mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cover.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish with additional chocolate crumbs if desired.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix ingredients one by one until everything is mixed.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top lightly with flour sifter.

title: spiced orange tea drink
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes nice gifts in decorated canisters.

title: chocolate fried pies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Combine egg and milk; add to dry mixture and mix well.
Roll dough to pie crust thickness.
Cut into saucer size circles.
Fill with chocolate mixture.

title: easy cold pizza(good hot too!)
directions: To thaw dough, place in refrigerator the night before in a covered bowl.
By morning, it will be thawed out.

title: tammy wynette's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco thoroughly; add eggs.
Blend rest of ingredients, one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Combine carrots, butter, lemon juice, salt and sugar in large saucepan.
Add just enough water to cover.
Bring to boil; simmer, covered, about 1/2 hour, then cook over high heat until liquid evaporates, stirring constantly with spoon.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook rice until almost done.
Cut up red onions very fine and brown in shortening.
Cut up giblets and put in with onions; cook until brown.
Add garlic, cut very finely.
Chop green onions with tops and parsley and add to the mixture along with salt, red pepper and water.
Pour over cooked rice.
When the water is absorbed, put in a large baking pan.
Dot with butter and brown in 350° oven for 15 minutes, if desired.
Serves 30 to 40 people.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Mix vinegar, celery salt, mustard seed, salt, sugar, red and black pepper and cold water.
Bring to boil; boil hard for 1 minute.
Pour hot mixture over tomatoes, green pepper and onion. Cover and place in refrigerator to chill.
Before serving, add cucumber.
Serve very cold as a salad on lettuce or as a relish. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
This may be made ahead and later transferred to a chafing dish.
Heat in pan first as candle will not be strong enough to melt cheese.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan over low heat.
Let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg. Beat well.
Mix together flour, baking soda, salt and all of the spices.
Add liquid mixture. Mix well and chill.
Form 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook meat and onion until tender.
Add browned bacon; drain any fat.
Blend flour and seasonings into meat mixture.
Stir in soup.
Cook slowly, uncovered, stirring frequently for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serves 6. Serve over egg noodles.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Crumble bacon and finely chop beef.
Sprinkle on flour and add milk.
Heat and stir until thickened.
Scramble eggs into 1/2 cup oleo.
Use a large deep dish casserole or pan, approximately 9 x 13-inch.
Layer sauce and egg, ending with sauce (usually 4 layers).
Cover, a must.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Can prepare day ahead covered and refrigerated.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: mother's granola
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Mix water, oil and vanilla in bowl and pour over the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in shallow pan and bake at 300° for 1/2 hour until brown.
Stir occasionally. Cool and store.

title: beignets
directions: In a small bowl, combine water, yeast and 2 teaspoons sugar. Let stand about 10 minutes, until yeast foams.
Meanwhile, combine milk, vanilla, butter, egg, 1/3 cup sugar, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in the yeast mixture.
Add the flour, one cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
After three cups have been added, knead in the remaining flour, 1 to 2 tablespoons at a time.
Knead until smooth, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in an oiled bowl, turning to coat.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down dough and roll to a 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut the dough into 2-inch diamond shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Pour oil to a depth of 3-inches in a heavy pot or fryer.
Heat to 365° and fry the beignets, 4 or 5 at a time, for 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towel and place in a warm oven while frying the remaining beignets.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving warm.
Makes about 30.

title: sour cream onion soup dip
directions: Mix sour cream and dehydrated onion soup thoroughly.
Let stand at least 1 hour before serving for flavor to blend.

title: apple cider molded salad
directions: Soak raisins in 1/2 cup apple cider.
Chop apples.
Prepare jello according to package directions except use apple cider instead of water, chill until slightly jelled.
Add chopped apples.
Drain raisins and add to jello, add chopped walnuts and put into jello mold.
When ready to serve turn out onto a plate and garnish with white grapes.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed on package.
Add pineapple, Cool Whip and rice.
Fluff and serve.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar gradually, then melted shortening, potato and milk.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Use donut cutter, drop into hot Criso or corn oil.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread; spread bread slices with butter. Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside. Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well. Spoon over bread slices; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt; mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover casserole and chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. Yields 10 servings.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour on a 17 inch cookie sheet.
Put drained pineapple on top of cake.
Mix pudding, cream cheese, and milk.
Pour on top of pineapple.

title: chicken with sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Brown garlic cloves in olive oil.
Add chicken; brown on both sides, 10 to 12 minutes.
Add broccoli florets, tomatoes, basil, red pepper flakes, white wine and chicken broth.
(Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.)
Cook pasta according to directions.
Serve chicken and tomatoes over pasta.

title: bachelor buttons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together brown sugar, butter (softened) and egg.
Add baking soda, water and flour.
Add raisins or nuts if you like.
Roll cookie dough in hand (about a teaspoon per cookie), then roll in cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Mix crabmeat, cheeses, onions and pimiento in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 minutes in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream well oleo and sugar; add eggs. Beat well. Add alternately sour cream and cake flour. Add baking powder, salt and vanilla; beat well. Place 1/2 mixture in tube pan. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture. Add remainder of cake mixture. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli-rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all of the ingredients; top with grated cheese.
Cook 15 minutes at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Add enough milk to corn liquid to make 1 cup.
In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, corn meal, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add corn, milk mixture and beaten egg.
Stir just until moistened.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and form into one-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on paper towels.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Heat soup, milk and chicken.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Add onions, celery and green pepper with other ingredients and place in casserole.
(Optional: Add 1 small package frozen English peas before placing in oven.)
Sprinkle with paprika and cheese or bread crumbs.
Cook at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Will serve 8.

title: hot fudge cake(easy and great!)
directions: Bring to a boil margarine, oil, cocoa and water.
Cool.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add cocoa mixture to flour mixture and stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for 30 to 35 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: deep-dish pizza
directions: Cook and stir hamburger until brown.
Drain.
Prepare pizza dough.
Mix tomatoes, onion, oregano, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and garlic powder.
Break up tomatoes with fork. Press dough into pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Spoon sauce onto hamburger.
Top with mushrooms and cheese.
Cook at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frying pan beans or cowboy beans
directions: In frying pan, cook bacon and onion until bacon is brown.
Add pork and beans, brown sugar and molasses.
Bring to a boil. Reduce to simmer and cook until thickened.
Tastes may vary, so feel free to add catsup, mustard or any ingredient you like in baked beans.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 2-inch deep oil to 375°.
Combine remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into hot oil, frying a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: "cheezy" chocolate fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese.
Add nuts, sifted sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes a lot.

title: cold-oven pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and oil together, adding eggs, one at a time, beating with each addition.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts; stir.
Mix flour and baking powder together; add to mixture, alternating with milk.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
While noodles are cooking, saute green pepper and onion in margarine.
Add soup, milk, sour cream, olives, salt, pepper and chicken.
Drain noodles and mix with mixture.
Put mixture into a 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with parsley and almonds (may use Parmesan cheese and/or bread crumbs also).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until almonds are lightly browned.

title: white christmas fudge
directions: Spread on buttered plate.
Cut when cold.

title: mary virginia's forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
Fold in vanilla, chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on foil-lined cookie sheet. Turn off oven and place in the oven; leave overnight or 8 hours. Makes 3 dozen.

title: risotto (rice with vegetables)
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Saute onions and carrots.
Add rice and saute until opaque.
Add bouillon cubes, bay leaf, salt, thyme and water.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in parsley.
Serves 12.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, removing bones from salmon.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: silver white cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and 2/3 cup of milk.
Beat 2 minutes. Add remaining milk, egg whites and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes. Pour into two greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.
Recipe makes good cupcakes.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Mix soup, water, celery, onion and stuffing.
Spoon into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Place chicken on stuffing mixture. Mix margarine, sugar and mustard.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken. Stir stuffing. If desired, garnish with chopped fresh parsley. Serves 4.
Preparation time: 10 minutes; cook time:
30 minutes.

title: brandied spaghetti sauce
directions: In medium saucepan saute celery, onion and garlic in the oil until onion is tender but not browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, herbs and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: nantucket cinnamon toasts
directions: In a wide, shallow bowl stir together sugar and cinnamon. With one strip of bread at a time quickly coat in butter, let excess drip off, turn quickly in cinnamon sugar.
Bake on lightly buttered baking sheet in upper third of 375° oven for 10 minutes. Turn over and bake 10 minutes more.
Serve warm.

title: manicotti with spinach
directions: Cook manicotti as directed on package.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, egg, onion, salt and Parmesan cheese.
Fill manicotti shells with cheese mixture. Place in lightly oiled dish.
Cover with marinara sauce.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cook spinach as directed on box and spoon on top of manicotti.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Reserve 1/2 cup to dredge fruit and nuts. Combine dry ingredients with creamed mixture alternately with the liquids.
Add fruits and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet and bake for 25 minutes in a slow oven.
Makes 200.

title: butter pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Place pecans and butter in a shallow pan.
When oven reaches 500°, turn it off and place pan in the oven.
When oven is cool, pecans are done.

title: borsch(beet soup)
directions: Make a beef bouillon with beef, 1 onion, 1 carrot and water. Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, making sure you have 1 quart of liquid at the end of cooking.
Meanwhile, chop beet, 1 carrot and 1 onion into long thin pieces.
Put tomato paste, fresh tomato, vinegar, sugar and 1 cup water into a separate pan.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Chop potatoes and carrots and add to boiling bouillon. Cook for 10 minutes.
Add done vegetables (beets, etc.).

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Steam spinach until done.
Place in blender with garlic, parsley, basil and oregano.
Process until mixed, not liquid.
In a bowl, combine wheat germ, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Add spinach mixture; stir to blend.
Cook noodles; add oil.
Mix Ricotta cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Preheat oven to 375°. Butter bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer first the noodles and spinach mixture, then Ricotta mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan, then Mozzarella.
Repeat.
Cover with remaining Mozzarella and tomato sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook onions in margarine and bacon fat 3 or 4 minutes.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Add potatoes; continue cooking, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes or until heated through.
Do not boil.
Add parsley and bacon. Cook about 1 minute longer.

title: chocolate mousse(serves 15)
directions: Warm eggs to room temperature (at least 1 hour).
Separate eggs.
Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler, stirring constantly, as it has a tendency to become grainy or lumpy. Remove from heat and add egg yolks, one at a time.
Mix until just smooth and let sit.
Beat whites until very stiff.
Fold into chocolate mixture using wire whisk, until very foamy and fluffy. Put this into the bowl you wish to serve it in and chill.
Make this at least one day ahead, preferably 2 days.

title: crunchy apple salad
directions: Place apples, bananas and lemon juice in bowl and toss.
Add pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Toss slightly.
Add mayonnaise. Toss just until mayonnaise is mixed thoroughly.

title: potato pancakes(potetpannekaker)
directions: As potatoes are grated, add milk at once to keep them from discoloring.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop spoonfuls on hot greased skillet and fry to golden brown on both sides.
Reduce heat after they are browned and cook until potatoes are done. Good with pork sausages.

title: chicken almond
directions: Mix all but potato chips.
Put in large baking dish. Refrigerate overnight.

title: california sweet potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Peel and halve lengthwise.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Mix brown sugar, cornstarch and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Blend in orange juice.
Add raisins.
Stir while bringing to a boil. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake uncovered for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: ranch snack
directions: In a large bowl, mix crackers and salad oil. Combine dry dressing mix, dill weed and garlic powder in a large brown paper bag.
Add crackers to mix in bag and shake.
Place in airtight container for at least 4 hours.

title: bacon-wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Combine sugar and catsup.
Wrap each whole chestnut with 1/2 slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Pour catsup mixture over top and bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: Add sugar to cooked rice.
In medium saucepan, combine dessert mix and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice mixture and raisins.
Let cool, stirring occasionally.
Pour into 6 dessert cups.
Refrigerate until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix together sour cream and the remaining 7 ingredients. Marinate chicken breasts in the mixture, refrigerated, overnight. Roll chicken in bread crumbs. Place in a 2-inch deep baking dish. Melt 1/2 cup margarine and 1/2 cup Crisco. Pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Remove from oven. Drain and bake 5 more minutes.

title: cranberry-cherry relish(chutney-like condiment)
directions: Combine all ingredients except cranberries in heavy large saucepan.
Bring mixture to boil over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add cranberries and simmer until they begin to pop, about 5 minutes more.
Remove cinnamon stick.
Cover and refrigerate until cold.
Can be prepared 1 week ahead of time.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; stir in cheeses. Stir in chopped pepper. Store in the refrigerator. Yield: About 4 cups.

title: ham and eggs au gratin
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not browned.
Blend in flour and salt; cook until bubbly.
Add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until melted.
Add eggs, potatoes, ham and parsley. Pour into 1 1/2 or 2-quart baking dish; top with remaining cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Garnish with additional egg slices. Yields 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt chocolate and margarine over hot water.
Combine sugar, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Cream 1 1/2 minutes.
Add cooled chocolate mixture and flour mixture.
Blend good.
Add nuts; pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: baked haddock
directions: Place Haddock blocks into a 9 x 13 pan. Spread mayonnaise on top of each block. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese. Add to bottom of pan, 2 Tbsp of butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Put all ingredients except apples, cinnamon and the 5 tablespoons sugar in a large bowl.
Mix well.
In another bowl mix apples, cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Put in tube pan (greased and floured) a layer of batter, 1 layer of apples.
Repeat ending with apples on top.
(Nuts may be added to last layer of apples.) Bake approximately 1 3/4 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Mix egg, shortening, buttermilk and vanilla; add to dry ingredients.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute, then on high speed for 3 minutes.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
(Muffin tins lined with cupcake papers work the best.) Bake approximately 15 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Top with Chocolate Frosting.

title: fruit cake saltine muffins
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Press into greased muffin tins. Bake in moderate oven at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: orange julius
directions: Put ingredients in blender.
Mix and serve.
Serves 6. Excellent for a Sunday Brunch!

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make coloring paste by mixing red food coloring with cocoa. Set aside.
Cream Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs and coloring paste and beat 10 minutes.
Mix in buttermilk slowly.
Add flour and salt.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir (with a spoon) in separately vinegar and soda.
Mix well and bake in 3 well-greased and floured 8-inch pans 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey dressing(for 20 pound bird)
directions: Put giblets in pressure cooker with 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook 15 minutes at 15 pounds pressure (or simmer until tender).
Remove bones.
Grind giblets.
Cool.
Save liquid.

title: barb's pumpkin delite
directions: Mix the pumpkin, eggs, milk, sugar and spices in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased 9x13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over the pumpkin mixture.
Melt the butter and drizzle this over the cake mix.
Top with pecans and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: mrs. gardner's strawberry cake
directions: Break cake into bite size pieces. Layer cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Spread strawberry glaze over cake.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and confectioners sugar together.
Spread some over glaze.
Alternate cake, glaze and Cool Whip mixture.
Top with fresh sliced strawberries, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable stock *
directions: Save in a large Ziploc bag.
When large Ziploc bag is full of vegetable scraps in your freezer, it's time to make stock.
Place scraps in large stock pot and fill with water.
Add spices and simmer 30 to 60 minutes.
Strain once through colander and once through finer strainer to remove all solids.
Freeze in ice trays and transfer to Ziploc bag for convenient small amounts.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring butter, sugar, cocoa and milk to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Spoon out on wax paper and let harden.
Ready to serve in minutes.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat milk and water until very warm (120° to 130°) and add to dry ingredients, beating well.
Add 1 cup whole wheat flour and then add remaining 2 to 3 cups flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon or spatula into 2 loaf pans that have been greased with Crisco and lightly sprinkled with cornmeal.
Then sprinkle cornmeal on top of the loaves.
Let rise in a warm place about 30 minutes or until dough is near the top of the baking pans.
Bake 22 minutes at 400°.

title: polynesian shrimp curry
directions: Combine milk and coconut in small saucepan; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Strain mixture; set milk and coconut aside.
Peel and devein shrimp.
Saute shrimp and pineapple chunks in 1/4 cup butter in large skillet 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink, stirring frequently.
Drain shrimp mixture and discard liquid.
Set shrimp mixture aside.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup butter and curry powder in large skillet; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Add green onions and celery; cook, stirring constantly until crisp-tender.
Combine flour and garlic salt; add to onion mixture.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add reserved coconut milk and chicken broth; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in shrimp mixture and reserved coconut.
Serve over rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: tuna log
directions: Beat tuna and cream
cheese together.
Add grated onion and salt.
Shape into log.
Wrap
with	plastic wrap and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Roll
in	pecans.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken ala diana
directions: Cut chicken in strips.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in scrambled egg and then bread crumb mixture. Fry chicken; brown.
Layer chicken and Muenster cheese and pour bouillon cube over.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°; turn often.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan, place chicken pieces to line pan.
Add grated Cheddar cheese and spread over chicken.
Add cream of mushroom soup (chicken) mixed with white wine or milk. Next, put Stove Top dressing mixed with melted butter, as per instructions on box.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until chicken is tender.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Beat thoroughly together (makes 4 layers).
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool completely.

title: chicken grape salad
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 1-inch chunks.
Toss chicken, celery and grapes in large bowl.
Season with thyme, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Mix in mayonnaise.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
Mix the envelope of soup mix (shake back and forth to get good mix for dip).
Blend soup mix into cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold in shrimp gently.
Keep covered in fridge.
Serve with Fritos or potato chips.

title: magic cookie bars(makes 24 to 36 bars.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish). In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven. Sprinkle crumbs over margarine; pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Cut into bars. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, layer cooked rice, then sausage and onions, then mushrooms.
Cover with grated cheese.
Mix soup and eggs in bowl and pour over layered ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 people (or 6 hungry people!).

title: "the best" brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in bowl.
Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture and blend well.
Add nuts.
Spread in 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until brownies pull from edge of pan. Cool in pan.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir in the hot jello and break apart with fork while stirring.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Pour into rectangular dish.
Congeal.
When set, spread with sour cream, if desired. Cut into squares and serve as dessert or on lettuce as a salad.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk in saucepan. Fold in tuna, peas and macaroni. Sprinkle potato chips on top. Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.

title: easy butterscotch cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and eggs and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine brown sugar, pecans and butterscotch chips and sprinkle over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: smoked beef cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mix with 2 packages of fine-cut beef, onion, Accent and sauce.
Roll on remaining package of cut beef. Can be divided to make 2 balls.
Chill.

title: lasagna rolls(no fat)
directions: Cook lasagna noodles, drain and cool.
Mix low-fat Ricotta cheese or light, spinach, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Spread spinach on noodles and roll up and cut in half.
Put ruffled edges up and line in dish, then pour sauce over the noodles and bake, uncovered, 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 18 rolls.
Serve with vegetable and salad.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oil in the blender until well blended.
Add oil.
Blend.
Chill and serve with favorite salad.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Bake pie crust at 450° for 5 minutes, then line with candy bars.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs, sour cream and peanut butter; pour over candy.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and whipping cream over low heat. Drizzle over warm pie.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add zucchini, oil, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Sift dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach pickles
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil except peaches.
Drop in a few peaches at a time until fork will prick peach easily.
Pack and fill jars.
Process 20 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: divinity
directions: Place in large pan, sugar, Karo, water and salt; stir until dissolved and it reaches boiling point.
Cover with lid and boil for 2 minutes.
Uncover and cook to hard boil stage.
Meanwhile, beat 3 egg whites.
Slowly pour hot syrup over beaten egg whites, beating constantly until cool and holds shape.
Add vanilla, walnuts and coconut.
Drop in greased buttered candy board or pour out on board and cut when cool.

title: crunchy casserole
directions: Lightly brown meat and onion in oleo, leaving meat in chunks. Spread in a shallow, 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, milk, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in partially frozen peas, celery and pimiento.
Pour over meat mixture.
Edge top of casserole with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: soda punch
directions: Mix equal parts of all sodas.
Make ice mold of ginger ale and fruit slices of your choice.

title: microwave brittle
directions: Combine in heatproof measuring bowl (2-quart) first 4 ingredients.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir; microwave for 4 more minutes.
Stir in next 2 ingredients.
Microwave for 1 minute.
Remove from oven; add baking soda.
Stir quickly and pour onto a buttered surface, cookie sheet or counter.
Cool; then break into pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Step One:
Combine soup, mayonnaise, celery, lemon juice and hard-boiled eggs, then combine chicken, rice and almonds.

title: quick heavenly hash
directions: Combine fruit cocktail, coconut, sour cream and sugar in a bowl.
Mix well.
Chill for 15 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans.
Mix dry ingredients. Gradually add moist ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: linda's banana nut bread
directions: Mix together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: haystacks
directions: Heat butterscotch chips and butter in a double boiler, stirring until smooth.
Add pecans and shoestring potatoes or chow mein noodles.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Place in refrigerator to harden.
Keep in covered container.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and cap mushrooms.
Use stems for another sauce or gravy; you do not use them.
Stuff the caps with the ground sausage. Sprinkle with bread crumbs, then the cheese.
Place in middle of oven and broil for 10 to 15 minutes, until meat is brown.
Serve warm.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Remove skin from chicken and dry thoroughly.
Mix mustard and butter.
Brush on chicken.
Place chicken pieces in a baking dish (meatier parts toward edge of dish).
Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook in microwave for 18 to 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Turn chicken pieces and rotate dish 1/2 turn after nine or ten minutes of cooking.
Let stand covered for five minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except food coloring in a mixing bowl; beat on low speed until blended; beat on high speed for 5 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Color as desired with food coloring.

title: shrimp noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients together, except 1/4 cup chow mein noodles.
Pour into greased, 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup noodles on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 3 servings.

title: witches brew
directions: Soften cream cheese:
Remove from foil wrapper and place on plate.
Heat 8 ounces for 15 seconds on full power.
Add 10 seconds at a time until softened as desired.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix in order given.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts together thoroughly, shaping into ball.
Chill several hours after.
Roll into nuts until covered.

title: brunch bake
directions: Stir together salt, eggs, dry mustard and milk. Tear bread into chunks and add to mixture.
Add cheese and bacon.
Stir together.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° in an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
For a nice change, you can add mushrooms and broccoli.
May be prepared the night before.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters and reserve liquid.
In baking dish, stir cracker crumbs, salt and butter. Stir until moist. Take half of mixture out and put into bowl.
Press remaining half in the pan. Cover with 1/2 of the oysters.
Sprinkle pepper over oysters, then cover with remaining half of crumb mixture and the rest of the oysters.
Combine cream, oyster liquid and Worcestershire sauce. Pour over dish.
Sprinkle with a few whole oyster crackers and dot with butter. Garnish with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Make sauce.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Remove from heat. Stir in flour, 3 teaspoons salt and the nutmeg until smooth. Gradually add milk and turkey stock; bring to boiling, stirring constantly; boil 2 minutes or until slightly thickened.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon grease and 1 tablespoon cornmeal, just until blended.
Heat bacon grease and 1 tablespoon cornmeal in cast-iron (10-inch) skillet until very hot.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: easy chocolate candy
directions: Heat chocolate bits and milk; stir over low heat until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat; stir in confectioners sugar and chopped nuts.
Chill.
Form into 1-inch balls and roll in finely chopped nuts, coconut or dipping chocolate.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream
together sugar, eggs, vanilla and butter.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Add apples, nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Spread mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chilled mexican appetizer
directions: Combine bean
dip,
tomato
paste
and	green
chilies; spread mixture in a 12-inch round platter with sides.
Combine chopped avocados,
tomatoes
and lemon juice; toss and arrange evenly over the
bean mixture; set aside.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix; spoon over avocado mixture. Combine green pepper,
green onions and ripe olives; sprinkle over sour cream layer.
Top with cheese.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yields 12 cups.

title: cheese frosted sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, boiled eggs, olives and mayonnaise.
Make 8 sandwiches with 3 slices of bread to each sandwich.
Beat cheese, raw egg and butter until fluffy.
Frost tops and sides of sandwiches with cheese mixture.
Make at least 24 hours in advance.
Can be made several days ahead and refrigerated.
Before serving, heat for 15 minutes in 375° oven that has been preheated. Cut each sandwich into quarters.

title: potato bake
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, bread crumbs, onions, milk, pepper and salt.
Drain potatoes and stir into egg mixture.
Add half of Cheddar cheese and half of bacon.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 8-inch square casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bacon; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: *Place head of cabbage in boiling water; cover.
Remove from heat and let stand until the leaves are limp (about 10 minutes). Remove from water.
Cut around stem end of cabbage to remove leaves; drain.
Pour 1/2 cup tomato sauce in bottom of ungreased 10 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion until tender in oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 cups.

title: play dough for children
directions: Mix the flour and alum in a large bowl. Cook water, salt and oil to boiling.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients.
Knead until smooth. Divide and knead in desired colors.
Store in airtight container.
Not to be eaten.

title: macadamia cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large bowl cream butter, shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until a soft dough forms. Stir in white chocolate and macadamia nuts.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Transfer to wire rack to cool.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Select center cut slices from an
18 month old ham (a 2 year old ham is even better).
Slice ham about 1/4 inch thick; trim off skin.
Place slices
in ungreased hot skillet and fry quickly on both sides.
Remove ham
to
hot platter and make a red eye gravy out of
drippings
by adding 4 tablespoons black coffee to skillet.
Let it sizzle up and pour over ham.
Serve with grits!

title: potato cake with peanut butter frosting
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in mixing bowl.
Stir in potatoes, then egg yolks.
Sift in flour, cocoa, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg; add milk.
Without prior beating, beat in egg whites. Continue beating well for at least 5 minutes or until batter is smooth.
Grease 3 (9-inch) layer pans.
Turn mixture evenly into 3 pans and bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until done. While cakes are cooling on wire rack, make Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crumble crackers in buttered 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over crackers and top with bacon bits.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serves 6 or 7.
Can easily be halved.

title: rio grande meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 37 5°.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
With moistened hands, shape into loaf and place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour pork chops with fruit
directions: Drain fruit, reserving juice. Moisten chops in 1/4 cup juice and coat with Shake 'n Bake as directed. Arrange chops in single layer in shallow baking dish; bake for 40 minutes at 425°. Combine 1/2 cup juice, brown sugar, catsup and vinegar. Heat through. Put fruit on chops and brush with syrup. Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add everything else, plus 1/2 can of water (tomato paste can).
Rinse each can to make the 1/2 can water.
Simmer about 2 or 3 hours.

title: original banana pudding(makes 8 servings)
directions: Reserve 1 banana and 10 to 12 Nilla wafers for garnish.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks thoroughly.
Add milk; beat again.
Sift flour with salt and 1 cup sugar; add to egg mixture.
Cook until thick. Add butter; let cool.
Add vanilla and coconut.

title: korean barbecued beef short ribs
directions: With bone side down, make a lengthwise cut in each piece, cutting beef halfway to bone. Cut crosswise at 1/2-inch intervals. Meat will look like a fan.
Combine remaining ingredients in a blender. Pour sauce over meat before broiling.
Place on hot grill and brown on all four sides.
Cook until brown and crusty.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake your potatoes in the microwave or oven. Slice potatoes in half. Scoop out pulp, keeping skins intact. Mash pulp in a medium bowl. Mix all other ingredients with pulp. Spoon potato mixture into shell of the potato. Sprinkle with cheese. Then bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Heat liquid, then add meat.
When hot, serve.

title: bonbons
directions: Pour molasses into a mixing bowl.
Stir in dry milk and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix together with hands until candy holds together.
Shape into little balls and roll in chocolate sprinkles, coconut, nuts or graham cracker crumbs.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add sour cream.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Add extracts.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until cake tests done. Cool in pan.

title: polish lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain well.
Layer 1/2 in casserole dish.
Top with drained sauerkraut.
Top with other half of meat and onion.
Sprinkle egg noodles on top (uncooked). Combine soups and milk and spread over mixture.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with 1/2 to 3/4 cup shredded cheese and cook for another 1/2 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into a greased loaf pan; bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: crescent-veggie bar
directions: Pat crescent dough in flat layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise until smooth and spread over cooled dough.
Chop vegetables and spread evenly over dough.
Cover with grated cheese, cut into squares, and serve.

title: helen's good nut bread
directions: Sift together flour,
powder
and salt, then set aside. Cream Crisco and
sugar,
then add lightly beaten eggs.
Start adding flour mixture,
then
cup
milk, nuts, more flour, then the rest of
the
milk.
(You
stir
this until blended.) Pour into greased loaf pan
and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. (Makes 1
big,
heavy
loaf.)
Best when served with butter.

title: potatoes in beer(low-fat recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use a 3-quart deep casserole to prevent boil over.
Coat dish with spray shortening.
Cover bottom with 1/3 potatoes.
Top with 1/2 onion.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons flour and 1/3 cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Continue layering as before.
Top with remaining potatoes and cheese.
Pour beer down sides of dish so as not to disturb layers.
Cover; bake 45 minutes.
Remove cover; bake another 20 minutes or until cheese is light brown on top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Spray foiled lined pan or baking dish with vegetable spray. Place floured small pieces, skin down in center of dish.
Larger (floured) pieces outside.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake about 1 hour, turning about halfway through baking time with tongs.
Bake at 350°, longer cooking time for larger fryer.

title: nacho dip
directions: Soften cheese spread in bottom of glass pie dish.
Pour can of chili on cheese spread.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: caramel pie
directions: Melt 24 Kraft
caramels in 1/3 cup of hot water.
Cool. Mix with 8 ounces
sour cream and 12 ounces Cool Whip.	Put in crumb crust and freeze.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain cherries and set aside. Drain pineapple and save juice. In a medium size bowl, place a layer of oranges, then coconut. Sprinkle some sugar, then a layer of pineapple. Sprinkle with cherry halves. Layer of coconut, then oranges and so forth until bowl is full. Pour saved juice on top and chill. Serve.

title: sandy gustafson's ham and cheese chowder
directions: Combine water, vegetables and seasoning.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Make white sauce of flour, butter and milk.
Add Cheddar cheese and stir until melted.
Add ham and undrained vegetables.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: hot or cold chicken 'n pasta
directions: In
large
bowl, mix mayonnaise, buttermilk, cheese and basil. Mix
in chicken, pasta and vegetables.
Chill at least one hour before serving.

title: garden medley soup
directions: Heat broth and add vegetables.
Cook until veggies are soft. Add Ro-Tel and cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Then add the lemon juice, salt and jello and stir to mix.
Chill until thick. Place strawberries in pie shell and pour partially set jello mixture over berries.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add mixture to Quick Mix and form a stiff dough that can be removed from mixing bowl in a single lump.
Place dough on lightly floured surface and knead briefly, using extra flour to keep dough from sticking to fingers or board.
Pat dough out onto a pizza pan.
Add pizza sauce and desired toppings and bake at 425° for about 15 to 20
minutes.

title: crisp apple dessert
directions: Put apple slices into pie pan.
Pour cinnamon and water over apples.
Prepare crumb topping by mixing together softened butter, sugar and flour.
Sprinkle crumbs over apples and bake at 350° until crispy, about 30 minutes.

title: fried cookies
directions: Combine in heavy pan the butter, sugar, dates and eggs.
Cook until well mixed and darker in color.
Cool and add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Grease hands and form into balls about the size of a walnut.
Roll in coconut or nuts.

title: baby carrots
directions: Cook carrots in 1 quart saucepan, with the apple juice and honey.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 20-25 minutes or until carrots are soft.
Serves 6.

title: ginger-lime chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Place it and other ingredients in large bowl.
Stir and make sure chicken is entirely covered by marinade.
Let sit at room temperature for 2 hours or in refrigerator for 4.
Grill over hot coals, about 5 minutes per side.

title: colene's chicken and gravy
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Heat shortening in a large skillet. Fry chicken until done.
Mix soup, milk and soy sauce together. Pour over chicken in skillet.
Simmer for about 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until chicken is tender.

title: sweet peanut treats
directions: In the top of a double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Spread half into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Chill until firm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat over 350°.
Quarter the biscuits.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a Ziploc bag.
Put biscuit quarters in Ziploc bag with cinnamon and sugar mixture and roll till coated.
Grease a bundt pan with shortening.
Put coated biscuit quarters in pan.
Melt oleo; add brown sugar and water.
Boil 2 minutes, pour over biscuits.
Bake 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Add to the above mixture.
Stir to blend.
Pour mixture into a flat pan.
Cool to set.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in bacon drippings.
Add soup and milk. Combine rice and broccoli.
Mix both mixtures together.
Put in baking dish and cover with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: apple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes in ungreased muffin pan.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone and cut in small pieces. Mix soup, poppy seed and sour cream together.
Mix with chicken.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbled crackers on top.
