Cook 1 hour at 350°. (This dish may be made ahead and refrigerated; bake when needed.)

title: corn sausage chowder(soup)
directions: In Dutch oven or kettle, cook sausage and onion until sausage is brown and onion is tender; drain on paper towel.
Return sausage and onion to Dutch oven with potato, salt, marjoram, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer just until potato is tender, about 15 minutes.
Add cream-style corn, whole kernel corn and evaporated milk.
Heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "daffodil" cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot pineapple juice.
Put 2 cups cold orange juice with juices.
When starts to congeal, beat in Cool Whip.
Place in bowl.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops.
Place crock-pot temperature on high.
Put pork chops in first.
Add water and pineapple.
Put a slice of pineapple on each pork chop. Cook until tender.
Delicious.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Place foil cupcake liners in muffin pan.
Place vanilla wafer or gingersnap in bottom of each liner.

title: homemade soft pretzels
directions: In a large bowl place 1/8 cup hot water from tap.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add warm water and brown sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add flour until dough does not stick to sides of bowl.
Place dough on a floured surface and knead until smooth. Pinch off dough the size of a golf ball and roll into a rope approximately 10 inches long.
Form into shape of pretzel and place on a floured surface.
Prepare cookie sheets sprayed with Pam. Fill frying pan with water.
For every cup of water add 1 tablespoon of baking soda.
Bring water to a slow boil.
Place pretzels into slowly boiling water for approximately 30 seconds. Place pretzels on cookie sheet and salt with Kosher salt.
Bake at 475° just until golden brown.
Pretzels are best if eaten right away.
They can be frozen after the frying pan step and baked from frozen at a later date.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Cut mushrooms into 1/8-inch slices.
Mix mushrooms and lemon juice in 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in oil, 1/4 cup parsley, salt, pepper, onions and garlic; toss.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally at least 3 hours.
Garnish with parsley before serving.

title: chicken in white wine sauce
directions: Heat large skillet.
Add margarine.
Brown chicken pieces, then remove to large casserole dish.
Rub flour into fat in pan. Slowly add chicken broth and white wine.
Add onions and carrots. Cook about 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken in casserole.
Add a large bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.
Serve with rice or buttered egg noodles.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Beer may be substituted for wine.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in mixing bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened.
Spoon batter into baking pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Turn out on rack.
Cool completely.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into patties.
If needed, add extra oats.
Cook in hot skillet in small amount of butter.
Brown on both sides.
Makes 3 patties.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Mix well with the cracklings. Add milk and beaten egg.
Mix well.
Put in greased pan.
Bake in hot oven 25 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Prepare Italian dressing as directed on package.
Slice onion in thin slices and separate slices.
In a pint size jar, alternate layers of mushrooms and onions and sprinkle with garlic powder. Pour Italian dressing
over
the mushroom/onion mixture and refrigerate at least
8 hours.
Shake often to mix spices.
Makes one pint jar.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli individually with 2 tablespoons water for 8 minutes in microwave.
Set aside and cool.
Take stick of butter, celery and onion and cook in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes.
Take butter, celery and onion mixture and add cut up cubes of cheese roll and mushroom soup.
Mix up and add broccoli. Heat in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cherry winks
directions: Cream shortening and cream cheese, gradually adding sugar. Beat well until light and fluffy. Add egg and almond extract, beating well. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to cream cheese mixture and beat well. Chill about 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in pecans. Place on ungreased cookie sheet; press 1/2 cherry into center of each cookie. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar glaze, if desired.

title: fruity chicken risotto
directions: Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Cook mushrooms, onion and bacon in oil over medium heat, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in water, soy sauce and bouillon.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: souper scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper to make sauce.
In a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange in alternate layers the potatoes, onion and sauce.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: delicious salmon loaf
directions: Pour salmon and juice into a bowl.
Add milk and bread crumbs. Mix well.
Add egg, onion, salt and chili powder.
Mix. Pour into well greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until center is firm.

title: triple layer bars
directions: Line a 9-inch square pan with graham crackers (spray first). Mix sugar, milk and margarine; bring to a boil.
Add crushed vanilla wafers.
Pour over graham crackers.
Melt peanut butter and chocolate chips together; spread over this.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Cool on counter.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and oleo.
Add sugar slowly.
Add one egg and a small amount of flour until all 6 eggs and flour are mixed in. Add flavorings.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured, at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Baking time is very important.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Boil noodles until done.
Drain.
Whisk oil, vinegar, salt, black pepper and paprika until well blended in large bowl. Add noodles and remaining ingredients. Toss gently until well blended. Cover and chill until ready to serve.
Toss gently before serving.

title: variable vegetable strata
directions: Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes.
Sprinkle half of the cubes into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle vegetables and cheese over cubes.
Top with remaining cubes.
Blend together eggs, soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour egg mixture over bread-vegetable mixture.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until golden brown, about 50 minutes.

title: summer strawberry soup
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan bring wine and ginger to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add heavy cream.
Return to boiling and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: turkey brunswick stew
directions: Combine in saucepan the broth, tomatoes with liquid, lima beans, corn, onion, ginger, bouillon cubes and pepper.
Heat to boiling; cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring as needed.
Add turkey and cook another half hour.

title: mom's homemade brown sugar candy
directions: Combine sugar, flour and butter in a large saucepan. Gradually add milk and mix thoroughly.
Bring this to a boil, without stirring unless it is sticking.
Reduce heat to medium and continue to boil until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove from heat, place in a pan of cold water to cool.
When cool enough, candy should have a grain to it.
Add vanilla, then beat until candy begins to thicken. Quickly add nuts and scoop candy into a buttered 9 x 13-inch cake pan and spread around.
Cut when cooled.

title: punch
directions: Mix well, serve over ice.

title: charmaine's monster cookies
directions: Mix in dishpan or roaster in order given.
Drop by ice cream scoop, 6 cookies to a tray or less, and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
(Recipe does not call for flour.)

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add all remaining ingredients except pecans.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into ball; roll in pecans.

title: granola
directions: Heat and combine honey and vegetable oil.
Pour slowly over remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 3 minutes.
Keep an eye on it!

title: linda's banana dessert
directions: Combine in bowl the flour, margarine and nuts.
Press in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: trifle
directions: In a large trifle bowl, cover bottom and sides with pound cake, soak with sherry and add fruit.
Make up jello according to directions.
Pour over fruit until covered (use leftover for kids).
Put in fridge to harden.
Make up custard omitting 1 cup of milk.
Pour in bowl, cover with plastic wrap and put in fridge for 1 hour.
Take out of bowl, mix custard, pour over jello and let settle.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pepernota pizza
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 1 tablespoon olive oil until lightly browned.
Set aside.
In another frypan saute peppers, wine vinegar, pepper and salt, if desired, until tender.
Spread pizza sauce on pizza crust, then onions, then peppers.
Bake at 400° about 8 to 10 minutes for prebaked pizza crust, 25 minutes for fresh pizza dough.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cook hen; chop and set aside.
Mix next 8 ingredients in saucepan and boil.
Combine cornstarch with enough water to make paste and add to vegetables; boil 1 minute.
Add chicken and cream of chicken soup to vegetable mixture.
Add water if needed.
Serve over rice and top with onion rings.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix in greased casserole dish all ingredients except the crumbs; sprinkle them on top and bake until brown at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Blend together in blender all the ingredients and pour into casserole.
Microwave 6 minutes at full power.
Serve immediately with corn sticks or crackers.

title: old fashioned peach cake
directions: Combine until crumbly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: round steak marinade
directions: Cut meat into bite-sized strips.
Place in airtight plastic container.
Pour remaining ingredients over top.
Mix thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.
Cook over campfire or under broiler.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger, rice, salt, pepper and onion and form into meatballs.
Mix together 1 can soup, 1 can water and chili powder to taste.
Pour over meatballs and simmer for 1 hour.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Food Process:
Put in bowl the cranberries (soak overnight or at least 2 hours in sugar), celery, apple and nuts.
Mix.
Set aside.
Make up jello (may use any red flavor) with juice of cranberries (about 1/2 cup) and orange juice instead of cold water.
Make jello by package but using juices to substitute cold water.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into jello mold sprayed with Pam oil spray.
Set overnight.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger. When meat is cooled, add other ingredients and mix lightly.
If too dry to spread, add small amount of tomato juice. Spread on butter buns. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: macaroni, tomato and cheese casserole
directions: Boil macaroni according to box directions.
Grate cheese; divide into thirds.
Drain canned tomatoes; save juice.
Chop tomatoes into bite size pieces.
In bottom of 2-quart casserole dish, layer 1/2 of chopped tomatoes, then 1/3 of cheese and 1/2 of cooked macaroni.
Repeat tomatoes, cheese and macaroni.
Pour juice over top of last layer of macaroni.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins first and let cool.
Use 1 cup of raisin water. Cream sugar and butter together.
Add beaten eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with raisin water.
Add cooled raisins. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: tara's favorite oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together. Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients. Add raisins last. Bake for 9 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in large bowl.
In saucepan, mix cocoa, margarine and water mixture to a boil.
Add this mixture to the sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk and vanilla and continue to mix well.
Add soda last.
Pour all into 16-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
This recipe will serve 10 people.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in greased 9-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven until top is brown and crusty, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon and allspice.
Add wet ingredients and stir until well blended.
Stir in oatmeal and raisins.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoons and bake slowly at 350° until lightly browned.

title: pizza casserole
directions: For first layer, cook noodles and drain.
For second layer, brown beef.
Add spices, onion, water and tomato sauce.
For third layer, cover with pepperoni.
For fourth layer, cover with cheese. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine self-rising corn meal, sugar and onion in bowl.
Add milk and egg to dry ingredients, stirring to combine.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful into hot deep fat (375°), frying only a few at a time.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: hot pizza dip
directions: In a bowl, combine cream cheese, Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Spread on bottom of greased 9-inch pie plate.
Combine cheeses.
Sprinkle half over the cream cheese layer.
Top with the pizza sauce and peppers.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheeses. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with tortilla chips or bread sticks.
Yield:
About 3 1/2 cups.

title: teriyaki beef broil
directions: Partially freeze steak, slice diagonally across grain into 1/4-inch strips.
Place steak in shallow container with soy sauce, vegetable oil, molasses, ginger, mustard and garlic.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Thread steak on 9-inch bamboo skewers.
Place skewers on lightly greased rack in a broiler pan.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 6 to 7 minutes, turning once.

title: herbed pot roast
directions: Heat frying pan.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put onion slices on top of meat; add wine and rest of ingredients.
If desired, add peeled halved potatoes, small peeled whole onions and carrots cut diagonally in 2-inch pieces during last hour of cooking.
Make gravy, using 1/2 cup dry wine to replace 1/2 cup of liquid.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk in a saucepan and boil 10 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Mix well. Pour into greased pan and chill.

title: quick brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients until completely mixed.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: pear pie
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan.
Pour batter over butter; pour pears and the juice (with water added) over batter.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour, sugar and salt together. Add to yeast; add shortening.
Stir well and roll out on a floured board.
Cut with a biscuit cutter.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake in a hot 375° oven until brown.

title: jim's baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, or just scrub and rinse.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to prevent knife from cutting through.
Put potatoes in baking dish; fan slightly.
Sprinkle with salt, butter and herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses. Bake potatoes for another 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly brown, cheese is melted and potatoes are soft inside.
Serve with bacon bits.

title: my mother-in-law's favorite dessert
directions: Cook tapioca in hot water (you may soak overnight) with salt in top of double boiler until transparent.
Add dates, brown sugar, flavoring and nuts.
Cool in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: raisin squares
directions: Mix ingredients together; add cooked raisins.
Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Ice while still warm with powdered sugar icing.

title: tomato soup florentine
directions: Cut tomatoes in chunks; takes 5 to 6 large fresh tomatoes. Remove cores and stew them over medium heat without adding water for 15 to 20 minutes.
In a saucepan, cook the onion and garlic in the butter with salt and pepper until onion is translucent.
Add herbs and saute a few more minutes.
Add cooked tomatoes, sherry and honey.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Add fresh chopped spinach for last 10 minutes of cooking time.
Serve with warm French bread.

title: western pralines
directions: In large (3 1/2 quart) heavy saucepan, combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Cook over high heat for about 5 minutes or to 210° on candy thermometer.
Stir often and scrape bottom of pan. Mixture will foam up!
Add butter and pecans.
Over medium heat, continue cooking, stirring constantly and scraping bottom and sides of pan until candy reaches soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and cool slightly, only 2 minutes.
Beat with spoon until thick and creamy.
Drop from tablespoon onto waxed paper or foil. Let cool.
Makes about 20.

title: banana muffins
directions: Blend sugar and margarine; add eggs and mix well.
Add vanilla and mashed bananas.
Add flour and soda.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes one dozen.

title: brown edge wafers
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Beat by hand.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.
Watch carefully.
Done when edge of cookie is slightly browned.
Makes about 35.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Boil over low heat until mixture is thick, stirring constantly.
Place in a dish alternately with pecans and vanilla wafers.
Yield: 4 to 5 servings.

title: grandmother's applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar and spices. Mix butter and applesauce.
Add to sugar mixture.
Mix soda and flour.
Add chopped nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.
Bakes nicely in an angel food pan or may be baked in a loop pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and simmer hamburger and pepper.
Add onion, garlic, salt and oregano.
Add tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Line strips of noodles on bottom of pan.
Layer meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese.
Top with another layer of noodles and repeat until everything is gone.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cheese is brown.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Put chopped rhubarb in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix sugar and jello together and sprinkle over rhubarb.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over sugar-jello.
Pour 1/2 cup over cake mix.
Shave butter and dot over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce raisin muffins(sugar-free)
directions: Mix egg, oil and applesauce.
Add and beat well the flour, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon batter into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dirty rice
directions: Place all in casserole dish, cover, cook at 350° for one hour or until rice is done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar over these.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg together with a fork until crumbly and sprinkle over apples.
Over all pour shortening (oleo).
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake in 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine refried beans and chilies. Spread on large serving plate. Combine sour cream and taco seasoning. Spoon over bean mixture, spreading evenly. Cover and chill several hours.
Just before serving, garnish with cheese, tomatoes, onions and olives. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: new orleans beans
directions: Combine in casserole or small pot or pan; cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Fry bacon.
Drain on paper towel.
In grease left from bacon, add chopped cabbage, sugar and enough water to cover cabbage.
Add Tabasco or red pepper to your taste.
Cook until water evaporates or cabbage is tender.

title: chinese chicken wings(portuguese)
directions: Mix the soy sauce and sweet and sour sauce together.
Pour over chicken wings arranged in a large cooking pan.
Marinate about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together; blend in.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: mock ham spread
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients together and stir in rest and serve with crackers.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a medium-size bowl, mix flour, baking powder, soda, spices and nuts.
In another bowl, blend oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla and carrots.
Add flour mixture and mix until thoroughly blended.
Generously grease pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (8 or 9-inch) rounds pans for 25 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Delicious with cream cheese icing!

title: arthur's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup of pecans in greased and floured tube cake pan and set aside. Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one egg at a time.
Beat well after each addition.

title: mock chicken luau
directions: Saute chicken pieces in a pot.
Add enough water to just cover chicken.
Simmer until chicken is tender.
Add spinach and soup. Continue cooking until mixture is thoroughly heated.

title: fresh zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together the sugar, eggs and oil. Add zucchini and pecans.
Sift together the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt.
Then blend them into the creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and raisins.
Grease a Bundt pan, tube pan or heavy iron skillet.
Spread in cake batter.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: stuffed flank steak
directions: Mix together hamburger and bread crumbs very well.
Put mixture in the middle of steak and roll up.
Tie.
Place in foil. Pour soup in the pan and bake your flank steak at 375°.

title: grandma miller's cucumbers and onions
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl. Cover with cold water and refrigerate overnight. Drain. Rinse with cold water and drain again.
Mix together the vinegar, sugar and sour cream. Pour over vegetables and stir. Add pepper to taste.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spam bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together, pour into baking dish and bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: black cow
directions: Fill a 14-ounce glass 1/3 full with root beer.
Add 1 scoop ice cream.
Pour in about 1/4 cup more root beer.
Add 2 more scoops of ice cream.
Pour in enough root beer to fill glass. Serve with club soda to add for extra carbonation, if desired.

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Mash artichokes.
Mix with cheese and mayonnaise.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: savory crescent chicken puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl blend cream cheese and 2 teaspoons margarine (reserve 1 teaspoon) until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients; mix well.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix in large bowl first four ingredients.
Include juice from pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Right before serving, crush cookies.
Fold in cookies and Cool Whip.

title: sauerkraut with wine
directions: Drain sauerkraut; soak in cold water for 1 hour.
Drain. Saute onion in margarine.
Combine all ingredients, peppering heavily, and simmer 1 hour.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil 5 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon soda.
Pour over popped corn. Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Can add peanuts.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: Pour sauce over shrimp and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a bowl.
Add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Bring 4 cups of milk to a simmer in saucepan.
Stir a small amount of hot milk into egg mixture.
Then stir egg mixture into hot milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool. Stir in cream and vanilla.
Pour into ice cream freezer container. Add milk to fill line.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix cucumbers with vinegar and salt.
Refrigerate overnight. When ready to serve, thoroughly blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Press all liquid from the marinated cucumbers and discard.
Stir the cucumber and cream cheese mixtures together. Serve with fresh vegetables or corn chips.

title: parmesan meat balls
directions: Mix together.
Handle gently and form into balls.
Brown in hot oil; remove.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour half batter in hot greased skillet; sprinkle grated cheese over batter.
Pour in remaining batter.
Bake at 400° until done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: *You may use 2 boxes of chocolate pudding.

title: hummus dip
directions: In a large bowl, crush garlic and salt together.
Add drained chickpeas, lemon (squeezed) and tahini sauce.
Mix with blender/hand blender or mixer until smooth.
Serve with Lebanese bread/pita chips.

title: country spareribs
directions: Brown the ribs in some oil and mix all the ingredients together; simmer in pan for 15 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cover pan when putting into oven.

title: one bowl brownie
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass baking dish).
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwaveable bowl on High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: hamburger dinner
directions: Shred cabbage and put half of it in a greased casserole.
Add half of the sliced potatoes and half of the hamburger.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over this and add the remaining half of the ingredients in the same manner.
Pour over milk and bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: macaroni cutlets
directions: Cook macaroni in 1-quart of water. Let it overcook until it almost flattens out. Add butter and milk and continue to cook. Add cheese, stirring continuously. After cheese is all melted, turn off heat and let set for a few minutes to insure that it is thick enough. Spread in pan about 1/4-inch thick and chill.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into walnut sized balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: smothered steak and mushrooms
directions: Cut steak into individual portion sizes.
Dredge in flour and brown in oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In same skillet or in a roasting pan, lay meat on bottom; top with onion and mushrooms. Add potato slices, if you like.
Top with soup.
Cover and cook at 300° for 2 1/2 hours or simmer on low in covered skillet.
Serves 4.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Put these in layers.
You can also use avocado dip in place of ripe avocados (it is already mixed up).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients and whisk well to dissolve sugar.
Place in a squeeze bottle or jar. Refrigerate unused portions.

title: souper burgers
directions: In skillet, cook beef and onion until beef is browned and onion is tender; stir to prepare meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add soup, ketchup and pepper.
Over low heat, heat through; stir often. Serve on buns.

title: hard candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water.
Stir over medium heat until dissolved.
Boil (without stirring) until the hard crack stage is reached.
Remove from heat after the boiling has stopped; add flavor.
Pour over greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break into bite-sized pieces.
Cover with powdered sugar to avoid sticking.

title: chile quesadillas
directions: Sprinkle 2/3 cup cheese onto each of 3 tortillas.
Top each with 1/3 of chiles and 2 tablespoons salsa.
Cover with remaining tortillas, pressing gently.

title: ham and potatoes casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and ham in buttered baking dish.
Stir milk into mushroom soup.
Add onion, salt and pepper to mixture.
Mix well; pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Remove cover after 1 hour to brown top.

title: lynn's potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except use only 1/2 cup of the butter and corn flakes.
Mix other 1/2 cup of butter with corn flakes to sprinkle on top.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add the milk, blending thoroughly into mixture. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into the pie crust.
Sprinkle with the peanuts.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for about 10 minutes before serving.
Top with chocolate syrup, peanuts and Cool Whip.

title: bessie stermer's wine vinegar garlic salad dressing
directions: Put all together in a bottle large enough to shake well, then shake.

title: punch recipe
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 cups hot water.
Add rest of ingredients and freeze.
Thaw 3 1/2 hours.
Add 1 (2 liter size) ginger ale.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Cool.
Sift flour with salt. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Cream butter.
Add sugar and continue beating until well blended and fluffy.
Blend chocolate; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla. Add flour alternately with buttermilk mixture, mixing well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: cranberry banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt-type pan; set aside.

title: cockeyed cake
directions: Sift flour and cocoa with remaining dry ingredients.
Sift this into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Make 3 wells (or holes) in flour mixture.
Into one, pour the oil.
Into another, pour the vinegar and into the next, pour the vanilla.
Pour the cold water over all.
Beat with a spoon until nearly smooth and you cannot see the flour.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine everything except chips.
Crumble chips on top when serving.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water, stir in orange juice and let congeal slightly.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise for dressing.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add remaining ingredients and store in tightly covered container.
Refrigerate.
Spoon mixture into greased muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Can be baked immediately without refrigeration.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until like coarse corn meal.
Add egg and rest of ingredients.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Drop by teaspoonful 1 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until done at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Knead.
Mix well. This is the recipe I use for molded mints.

title: best salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones and skin.
Mix with beaten eggs, butter, hot milk and corn flakes.
Season with garlic salt, onion and pepper.
Mix and put in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade "shake 'n bake" mix
directions: Mix all together.
Store in a tightly covered container in refrigerator.
This equals 20 bags of store bought bags of chicken coating.
Use on pork, too.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Mash potatoes.
Stir in the nutmeg.
Shape into balls around each marshmallow.
Roll in melted butter, then in corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen.
Wrap tightly and store in freezer.

title: bruschetta
directions: Preheat the oven on broiler setting.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the roma tomatoes, sun-dried tomatoes, garlic, olive oil, vinegar, basil, salt and pepper. Allow the mixture to sit for 10 minutes.
Cut the baguette into 3/4 inch slices.

On a baking sheet, arrange the baguette slices in a single layer. Broil for 1 to 2 minutes, until slightly brown. Divide the tomato mixture evenly over the baguette slices. Top the slices with mozzarella cheese.
Broil for 5 minutes, or until the cheese is melted.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Drain. Cook macaroni and drain. Combine hamburger, macaroni and pizza sauce.
Layer in casserole half the hamburger, macaroni mixture, half the pepperoni pieces and half the cheese.
Repeat layers, topping with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut corn flake macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add salt and gradually add sugar, beating until dissolved. Fold in remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 1/2 hour (30 minutes) in a 325° oven.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to 239°.
Start the beater and slowly pour 1/3 of the syrup over the unbeaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Cook remaining syrup to 255°.
Add 1/2 of the syrup to the egg white mixture, beating constantly.
Cook remaining syrup to 290°.
Add vanilla.
Add to egg white mixture. Beat until mixture holds shape when dropped from spoon.
Add nuts or candied cherries if desired and drop candy from spoon to form puffs.

title: orange sherbet jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 7-Up and juice from mandarin oranges.
Chill until partially thickened.
Add oranges and orange sherbet.
Beat until frothy.
Chill until thickened.

title: pasties
directions: Mix ground chuck, potato and onion together in bowl, then shape into 2 loaves.
Place loaf on pastry, tart style, fold pastry over top of loaf and seal edges.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine first 7 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Stir in pecan halves. Spread on 2 (10 x 15-inch) baking sheets.
Bake for 1 hour. Remove to waxed paper to cool.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: summer berry pie
directions: Mix all berries in a large bowl.
Pour in pastry shell.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Stir in water gradually until smooth.
Cook, stirring constantly, on medium heat until mixture comes to boiling point.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in jello until dissolved.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over berries in pastry shell.
Refrigerate 3 hours until set. Serve with topping.

title: cherry topped cheese pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into unbaked graham cracker crust.
Top with pie filling.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the ingredients thoroughly, except for the egg whites and 4 tablespoons sugar; cook at medium heat until it thickens.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole dish with olive oil. Layer sliced tomatoes and onions in dish.
Sprinkle cheese, salt, bread crumbs and pepper on top.
Bake about 1 hour or until onions are done.

title: white cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Sift together the flour, 2 teaspoons baking powder and salt.
Add to Crisco mixture with water.
Beat into batter.
Beat 1 teaspoon baking powder with egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake in 3 greased layer pans at 375° for 25 minutes or in a 9 3/4 x 13 x 2 1/4-inch oblong cake pan for 30 minutes.

title: delicious topping for german chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar, milk, egg yolks and shortening in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Cook for 15 minutes. Spread only between layers and on top of cake.

title: easy ambrosia salad
directions: Drain all fruit; mix with sour cream.
Add coconut and marshmallows.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: sauce for party links
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, dry mustard, soy sauce, pineapple juice and vinegar.
Heat to boil.
Let boil 1 minute.
Add sausage and heat a little more.
Serve from chafing dish.
One recipe will do a 2-pound party pack, approximately 109-count.

title: darla's special chicken enchilada bake(this is a delicious main dish.)
directions: *This should make 2 cups of cooked chicken for recipe.

title: barbecue lasagna
directions: Use large size cooking pan, approximately 10 x 14. Grease the bottom of pan with cooking oil. Put in the layer of chicken. Sprinkle a layer of flour on the chicken. Cover it with a layer of celery, then a layer of chopped onions. Melt 1 stick or margarine and pour into the pan. Then pour in a 10 3/4 ounce can of cream of mushroom soup. Season with pepper and salt. Cook for approximately 90 minutes at 350°.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water; add berries and pineapple. Congeal overnight.
Add topping of softened cream cheese, sugar and sour cream; blend.
Spread on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Sift together remaining ingredients.
Mix well with pumpkin mixture.
Pour into 2 large greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
You can use the Pam spray or the cooking and baking spray.

title: block party beans
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat and spoon off fat.
Add onions and celery; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, paste and catsup; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour, or use crock-pot for several hours. Do on stove top for 1 hour and then crock-pot.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine and pour into large, shallow Pyrex dish.
Stir into margarine uncooked rice.
Stir until even and all rice is moistened.
Place uncooked chicken parts on top of rice (salt and pepper chicken).
Cover with mixture of water and cream of mushroom soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken and beef
directions: Wrap bacon around each piece of chicken.
Line an 8 x 8-inch shallow baking dish with chipped beef.
Place bacon-wrapped chicken on top of beef.
Mix soup with sour cream and spread over chicken. Sprinkle top with paprika.
Do not salt.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Make pie crust by mixing cracker crumbs, butter, salt and flour.
Press in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Melt together in a double boiler the milk and marshmallows.
Cool. Add whipped cream and fruit cocktail.
Pour into pie shell and garnish with 2 tablespoons reserved graham cracker crumbs.
Chill for several hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Stew chicken.
Debone chicken and chop in small chunks.
Add soups, Ro-Tel and rice to broth.
Bring to a boil.

title: quick macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on package, then add and mix all additional ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops in small amount of shortening.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place chops in greased baking dish.
Top each chop with a tablespoon of rice.
Place tomato slices, onion slices and green pepper on rice.
Spoon tomatoes over all.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and continue baking for 30 minutes longer. Makes 4 servings.

title: green salad(cookbook winner, 1992)
directions: Mix pudding and undrained pineapple together.
Stir in whipped topping, fold in marshmallows and chill.

title: best in the west barbecue bean bake
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion; drain excess fat.
Combine and add all other ingredients, except the beans; stir well.
Add beans; combine thoroughly.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: round steak barbecue
directions: Spread steak with prepared mustard, flour and brown.
Combine ingredients, pour over steak and simmer 2 hours or until tender. Serve with mashed potatoes, rice or spaghetti squash.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add peanut butter, eggs, buttermilk, water and vanilla.
Add this to flour and baking powder mix.
Combine and beat very smooth.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: hot buttered rum mix
directions: Blend butter and sugars, using an electric hand mixer.
Stir in the soft ice cream and place the container in freezer.
This recipe makes 6 cups of mix, enough for 48 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind berries and sugar.
Let set overnight.
Next day, drain well.
Mix with other ingredients.
Whip cream and fold together. I usually make a double recipe and I also use chilled can cream instead of whipping cream.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Scoop out insides of potatoes, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Mash potatoes with milk in a bowl.
Stir in broccoli or spinach, cheeses, garlic, salt and pepper.
Spoon filling back into potato skins.
Sprinkle with more grated Parmesan cheese (about 2 tablespoons) and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: so different rhubarb pie
directions: Combine egg yolks and next four ingredients into bowl; mix well.
Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar until stiff peaks form. Fold gently into the egg yolk mixture.
Fold in rhubarb.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake for 45 minutes longer.

title: no boil lasagna(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and 1 cup water; bring to a boil.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta and egg.
Add Mozzarella, 1/3 cup water, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes, sugar, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Rinse uncooked lasagna in hot water and place 3 to 4 strips in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour 1 2/3 cups meat sauce over lasagna. Layer 1/2 cheese mixture, 1 1/2 cups sauce, 3 to 4 strips lasagna, remaining cheese mixture, 1 2/3 cups sauce, remaining lasagna strips and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven until lasagna strips are tender, about 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake an additional 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain.
Set aside.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles, place on a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press bottom and sides to form crust; seal perforations. Bake at 375 degrees for 5 minutes.
Crust will be puffy.
Reduce temperature to 350 degrees.
Spoon sausage over dough; sprinkle with cheeses.
Combine eggs, milk, oregano, and pepper; pour over sausage.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: low-fat pineapple angel food trifle
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits, reserving 1 cup juice; set aside. Combine instant pudding mix, 1/2 cup reserved juice and milk in a large bowl.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer 2 minutes or until thickened.
Fold in sour cream and pineapple tidbits.
Place 1/3 of cake cubes in bottom of a 16-cup glass bowl.
Drizzle with 2 to 3 tablespoons remaining reserved pineapple juice.
Spoon 1/3 of pudding mixture over cake.
Repeat procedure twice, ending with pudding mixture.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Just before serving, spread top with whipped topping.

title: cheese ring
directions: In large bowl, mix cheese, mayo, nuts, onion, pepper and Tabasco. Form into a ring on a platter. Cover and chill.

title: date nut fruit cake
directions: Chop dates and pour the 1 1/4 cups of hot water over them and set aside to soak.
In a large bowl cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dates and warm water that they have been soaking in. Add vanilla, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Then add flour and pecans. Add cherries (with juice), raisins and candied pineapple.
Mix well.
Put in a 12 cup tube pan with floured sides and a waxed paper ring in the bottom.
Bake at 325 degrees for 2 hours.
DO NOT PREHEAT OVEN.
Upon removal, wrap immediately in foil.

title: mexican party chicken
directions: In a sauce pan, combine chicken, chilies, enchilada sauce and soup.
Heat until boiling.
Place 1/3 corn chips in bottom of a greased baking dish.
Alternate with layers of chicken mixture, onion and cheese.
Top with remaining chips.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: wilma's pound cake
directions: Cream shortening in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating continuously.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until light and fluffy.
Add flour and milk alternately, beating well after each addition and adding baking powder and salt with last flour addition.
Beat in flavoring and continue beating for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into greased, waxed, paper-lined tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan to cooling rack.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: homemade pickles
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Fit cucumbers into two quart jars.
Pour in enough of vinegar mixture to cover cucumbers. Tighten lid and refrigerate for 1 week to develop flavor.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Add flour to sugar.
Pour in juice and rind of lemon.
Beat egg yolks and add with milk to lemon mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in lightly greased casserole with pan of water.
Bake at 300 degrees for one hour.
Watch carefully for when it is brown and the pudding is set.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, butter and chocolate chips together over low heat.
Let cool slightly.
Pour over Crispix cereal. Mix well.

title: aunt estelle's homemade syrup
directions: Add 1/2 cup water or more to dissolve sugars; add maple flavoring.
Boil to thin syrup.
Remove from heat.
Stir in white syrup.
This will not crystallize and will keep a long time.

title: self crust pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except water together in a large bowl. Stir in water gradually until well mixed.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted 1 inch from center comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.
Contains 150 calories per serving.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain.
Add Ragu, Hunt's and mushrooms and mix.
Cook shells until tender.
Spread layer of shells, sour cream and cheese.
Alternate until all is used, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
The more cheese the better!

title: mammoe's old fashion molasses taffy
directions: Combine sugar, molasses, butter and vinegar in saucepan.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil slowly constantly, toward end of cooking to 260° (or when small quantity dropped into cold water forms very hard balls).
Remove from heat. Pour into greased pan.
Cool enough to handle.
(Grease hands.) Form mixture into balls.
Pull until light yellow in color. Stretch into long rope.
Cut into small pieces.
Wrap each piece in waxed paper.

title: taco taters
directions: Bake potatoes until done (a fork will easily be pushed into the center or about 1 hour at 400° or microwave 4 to 5 minutes).
Split potato open and ruffle with fork.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Top with ground beef, salsa and cheese; melt cheese in oven or microwave for an easy quick meal.
May use variation with Manwich or jalapeno Cheddar dip.
Serve with corn chips.

title: easy mexican dip
directions: Pour salsa over cream cheese; use spreader or chips to dip.

title: chocolate rum cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and half of the chips and nuts. Beat.
Fold in rest of chips and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: crab mousse
directions: Heat soup; add cream cheese.
Add gelatin.
Cool mixture.
Add vegetables, mayonnaise and crab.
Season with Tabasco sauce, garlic salt and parsley to taste.
Put into greased 4 cup mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold onto platter lined with lettuce leaves.
Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
In a quart casserole dish, combine sauteed onion and eggs; add bread crumbs.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Drain corn.
Add egg yolks, milk, flour and butter.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in moderate oven until firm, about 1 hour.

title: bekah's fruit salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix with fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: zucchini pizza style
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip in beaten egg, then coat with bread crumbs.
Brown lightly on both sides in hot oil. Overlap slices in a lightly buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: batter fried vegetables
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; stir in water and egg until smooth.
Dip vegetables a few at a time into batter.
Fry in hot oil (375°)
a few pieces at a time until golden brown and crisp. Drain on paper towels.

title: granny's popovers
directions: *Have at room temperature.

title: pumpkin cake squares
directions: Beat with fork until cake is absorbed.
Press into bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter and cook until mixture melts. Stir in spinach and next 6 ingredients.
Set aside.
Place half of artichoke hearts in greased 2-quart casserole dish; top with half of the spinach mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: united nations casserole
directions: Dissolve bouillon in water; add salt. Bring to boil, stir in rice. Reduce heat and simmer, tightly covered, about 25 minutes. Add mushrooms, curry powder, parsley flakes and nutmeg.
Arrange chicken breast on top of rice.
Sprinkle liberally with paprika. Bake, uncovered, 350° 1 1/4 hours, or until chicken is tender.
8 - 10 servings.

title: meat loaf in a crock-pot
directions: Mix all ingredients together good.
Spray crock-pot with Pam. Put meat loaf into crock-pot and cook on high for 4 to 6 hours until done.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage and caraway seed in broth just until cooked down a little.
Cook bacon until crisp; crumble.
Saute garlic and onion in large frying pan.
Add cabbage and bacon and fry just until it still has a little crunch (like stir-fry).

title: rhubarb strawberry pie
directions: Place rhubarb and strawberries in unbaked pie shell.
Pour flour and sugar over fruit.
Dab butter around top of pie shell. Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put into a loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.
Cool a few minutes for easier serving. This will serve 6 to 8.

title: beef casserole
directions: Arrange in dish in layers all ingredients,
except soup, after layer is arranged add part of soup. Arrange layer again and finish off with remainder of soup.

title: bacon 'n' beans
directions: Fry bacon after cutting in small pieces.
Add bacon, onions and drippings to beans; heat to boiling point.
Serve hot.
Also good using fresh beans.

title: oriental dressing
directions: Combine in blender and process.
May need to double, triple, etc. recipe to get desired amount.
Great marinade for chicken or beef stir-fry.
Also good dressing for vegetable pasta salad (top with toasted sesame seed).

title: spice squares(low cholesterol)
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Boil 3 minutes in pan large enough to mix everything.
Cool, then add oil.
Mix together the soda and 1 tablespoon warm water.
Add to first mixture.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add walnuts.
Mix all with wooden spoon right in pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: roast potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix oil, garlic, salt and pepper in 9-inch square baking dish.
Add potatoes and turn to coat with oil.
Bake until tender and browned, 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bundt pan cornbread
directions: Mix together sugar and oil. Add milk and eggs. Add corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Finally add shredded Cheddar cheese, creamed corn and green chilies.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in a bowl. Mix the sugar and mayonnaise together. Stir this into the pea mixture. Mix well. Top with Parmesan cheese and refrigerate about 2 hours before serving.

title: crock-pot beef tips
directions: Brown beef tips or sirloin tips.
Place in bottom of crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients, cover and cook on low 8 to 12 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: helen's apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Beat together egg and milk and add, stirring quickly until dry ingredients are thoroughly moistened.
Spread in pan (13 1/2 x 8 3/4-inch).
Peel and core apples.
Slice from blossom to stem, making 1/2-inch thick slices.
Stick these end down into the dough very close together.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; dust over apples. Sprinkle over the nuts.
Cover the pan and bake in oven (350° to 375°) for 15 minutes.
Remove cover and continue to bake until apples are done.
Serve warm.

title: international sandwich
directions: Spread	the
bread with mustard.
Put bologna on bread; top with
spinach.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Place sandwich on paper or china plate.
Microwave 2 minutes, giving sandwich 1/2 turn after 1 minute.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer cheese over cooked macaroni.
Mix milk and egg and pour over macaroni and cheese and bake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and form ball.
Roll in chopped nuts or parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: mexican chicken dish(serves 8)
directions: Mix chicken, cream cheese, salsa and any other veggies you desire (green peppers, jalapeno, etc.). Take flour tortilla shells and put about 2 tablespoons of mixture inside shells.
Roll and line them up in a pan. Pour melted Velveeta cheese mixed with salsa.
Heat in oven for 15 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: party mix
directions: Melt margarine and bacon grease in a large roaster.
Mix well. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 250° for at least 1 hour. Stir often.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Beat egg yolks lightly with beer; add flour and salt.
Stir in melted butter and let set for 1 hour. Add egg whites gently into batter.
Coat fish and deep fry until golden brown.

title: brown stew
directions: Put shortening in Dutch oven or heavy bottomed pot with cover. When this is very hot add the beef a few pieces at a time so they will brown on all sides.
Remove.
When the last batch has been browned, return all to the pot and add 4 cups boiling water.
Stir and add all the ingredients with the exception of the carrots, onions and potatoes.
Lower the heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add other ingredients and cook for another 20 to 25 minutes or until they can be pierced with a fork.
Remove meat and vegetables to a casserole while putting finishing touches to the gravy.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Saute broccoli and onion in margarine.
Combine muffin mix with other ingredients.
Fold in sauteed mixture.
Bake in greased baking dish or pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Muffin tins can be used.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and drain, then add to sauce. Do not cover. Cook slowly.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Spray casserole pan.
Layer bread.
Brown and drain sausage. Put on top of bread.
Layer cheese.
Beat eggs and mix with mustard, soup, salt and milk.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a bowl.
Press into round cakes.
Place cakes into a hot, oiled frying pan.
Let cakes brown on both sides.
Drain.
Serve hot.
Delicious with a dash of hot sauce.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In an 8-quart kettle over medium heat, cook bacon until lightly browned.
Add onions and fry until tender, about 10 minutes.
Gradually stir in flour until mixed well.
Add enough water to clam liquid to make 4 cups.
Slowly stir it into flour mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Dump in potatoes, pepper and garlic.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add clams, milk, cream and butter.
Simmer until thoroughly heated, about 5 minutes, stirring often.
Makes 14 cups.

title: peanut butter crunches
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Blend in peanut butter.
Continue stirring.
Put corn flakes in a well-greased bowl and pour mixture over cereal.
Cool and then shape into balls.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 2 sticks of melted butter and 7 tablespoons of sugar in long Pyrex dish.
Cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Set it in refrigerator after done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water until cool.
Dice tomatoes, onion and bell pepper.
Combine with macaroni.
Add mayonnaise, 3 to 4 tablespoons or enough to blend. Add celery salt and pepper to season to taste.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: sour cream devil's food cake
directions: Pour boiling water over soda; let cool.
Cream sugar, cream and eggs together.
Add flour, salt, cocoa, sifted together soda mixture, cake coloring and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly with electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Pour into well oiled and floured oblong baking pan.
Bake in moderate oven about 40 minutes at 350°.
When cool, ice with chocolate frosting.

title: concombre choses
directions: Take one slice of pumpernickel bread.
Spread with approximately 1 teaspoon of cream cheese.
Place 1 slice of cucumber over cream cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cold pineapple pie
directions: Mix crushed pineapple, juice and pudding.
Add Cool Whip. Pour into baked shell.
Top with more Cool Whip and refrigerate until served.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Form into small balls.
Press down with glass over wet cloth.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Decorate with colored sugar or as desired.
(Do not bake until brown.)

title: galaxie cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except nuts.
Put into baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool, roll into ball and then into pecans.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook hamburger in butter until brown. Drain grease.
Return to pan and add salt, pepper, garlic and tomato paste.
Simmer for 1 minute.
Add sour cream and cottage cheese.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Cook potatoes with jackets on.
Peel and mash until smooth. Add sifted powdered sugar to make a dough.
Roll out on a biscuit board about 1/2 inch thick.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up and let set about 1 hour, then slice.

title: gumbo
directions: Bring beef, onion, tomatoes, water, chicken broth and bouillon cubes to a boil; simmer for 1 hour.
Add lima beans and cook for 30 minutes.
Add okra, ham and chicken.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes in small chunks. Cook until done, keeping them covered with water. Cook onion in with potatoes. Do not drain water. Add soups and milk. Stir well. Cut Velveeta in chunks and add to potatoes. Stir continuously until cheese melts. Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: fiesta corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Use an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Melt shortening in pan in oven.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to melted shortening and remaining ingredients.
Mix until just blended.
Pour into pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli as directed, then add the mayonnaise, onion, grated cheese, eggs, soup and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Mix the stuffing mix with the melted butter.
Put over top of broccoli and bake another 2 to 3 minutes or until brown.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Beat eggs and stir all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked 9 inch pie crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Stir cottage cheese in dry Jell-O.
Add oranges and pineapple. Add Cool Whip.
Mix together.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: orange-cashew chicken salad
directions: Peel and separate orange into sections and cut each section in half. In a large bowl, combine orange, chicken, pea pods, red pepper and onion rings.

title: easy herb and cheese spread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Put in bowl.
Sprinkle with pepper and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers and fruit.

title: creamed chipped beef over hot baked potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes as usual for baking in conventional oven. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then pierce 2 to 3 times with a fork. Continue baking an additional 30 to 40 minutes, until done.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, brown the ground beef and onion.
Drain. Add cabbage and cook until wilted.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: hot chili
directions: Combine meat, onion and garlic in a large skillet.
Cook until meat is light brown.
Add remaining ingredients (except for beans) and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add beans (as many as desired) and heat until hot.
Recipe may be halved. Serve with grated cheese, lettuce and sour cream.
Good with Mexican corn bread.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco.
Add sugar gradually, creaming well. Add egg yolks, beating well.
Add soda to buttermilk, mixing alternately with flour to sugar mixture and beat slowly.
Add coconut and pecans, then fold in beaten egg whites.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes or until done, using layer cake pans.

title: spicy hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight jar.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Boil chicken and season with salt and poultry seasoning.
Tear chicken from bone.
Place chips in casserole dish.
Leave enough for top.
Place chicken on chips.
Mix soup, tomatoes and onions together and pour over chicken.
Pour grated cheese over soup mixture and add crushed chips over top.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: chicken marengo(serves 8)
directions: Brown chicken in shortening.
Remove.
Add next 3 ingredients and saute until golden.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken and wine. Simmer 40 to 45 minutes until tender or use crock-pot.

title: crunchy cinnamon pecans(low carb)
directions: Melt butter in microwave 25 seconds. Mix sugars and cinnamon and mix well. Add melted butter and mix well. Add pecans and mix until well coated. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 30 minutes in 250° oven. Remove from oven; cool on wax paper. Place in Ziploc bag to stay fresh.

title: croute provencale(serves 4)
directions: Mince the onions and saute them in 3 tablespoons of olive oil until tender and lightly browned.
Add the tomatoes to the pan and season with salt and pepper; mix well.
Add the thyme and green pepper and cook the mixture, stirring constantly, until all of the liquid has evaporated and the mixture is thick.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at once on high speed until well mixed. Cook in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop first 4 ingredients.
Leave 1 hour.
Drain.
Put vegetables on stove and add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Pack in jars and seal.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream with mixer; pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
When cake is done, punch holes in cake with fork and pour coconut cream and Eagle Brand milk over cake.
When cool, frost with Coconut Frosting.

title: ricotta creme
directions: Place Ricotta in a fine strainer and drain the liquid.
Place all ingredients in food processor or blender and blend just to combine.
Spoon mixture into parfait glasses.
Chill.
Garnish with a fresh, thinly sliced orange ring and a sprig of fresh mint.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Toss vegetables.
Combine rest in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour over vegetables. Chill for 24 hours.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350°
until done.
Great with coffee.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well and shape into meatballs. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, depending on the size of the meatballs.
Mix the next 3 ingredients well in a large frying pan for gravy.
Cover.
Heat until bubbly and add meatballs, stirring occasionally so the gravy doesn't stick to the bottom of the pan.
These freeze well and can be added to spaghetti sauce or sweet and sour sauce.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in a large pot.
Add garlic, onion, celery and parsley. Cook until soft. Stir in tomato paste and next 7 ingredients.
Mix well. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer slowly 1 hour. Add remaining ingredients and cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: To make crust:
Scrape off sandwich cookie fillings.
Crush the cookies and combine with melted butter.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.

title: khajur ki chutney
directions: Put all the ingredients in a blender and mix well. Sieve and throw out the residue. Serve the strained chutney with kababs, tikkas.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients until blended.
Place in ungreased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chutney salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, chutney, curry powder, lime peel, lime juice and salt and let stand in refrigerator.
Cut pineapple in small pieces and drain thoroughly.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix beef, soup, eggs and oatmeal.
Roll into small balls.
Put in roast pan.
Mix Vernors and ketchup.
Pour over meatballs. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Cover first 2 hours, then uncover last hour to thicken.
Stir occasionally.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cook beef in large skillet or kettle until half done. Add onion and pepper. Cook until all is done. Press and drain grease. Add all soups and mushrooms to mixture and heat to a slow boil. Remove from heat and add sour cream. Stir well and serve over noodles.

title: italian meatballs with spaghetti
directions: Cook onion in hot olive oil until golden brown, add mushrooms and brown slightly.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, sugar, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and bay leaves.
Cook slowly 1 hour.
Combine meats and the next 6 ingredients; form into small balls.
Brown in a small amount of hot olive oil.
Drain meatballs on paper towels.
Add meatballs to sauce and cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: best beets
directions: Place hot beets in serving dish.
Pour French dressing over beets; toss lightly.
Top with sour cream; sprinkle with onions. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Bring water and salt to a boil; add rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand until water is gone. Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix onion, rice, broccoli, soup and Cheez Whiz in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine(for real men)
directions: Cook and crumble bacon.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium sized bowl, beat eggs, cream, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Layer crumbled bacon and cheese in pie shell.
Pour egg and cream mixture over it.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until quiche is golden brown or puffy.
Let cool for a few minutes before serving. Refrigerate leftovers and heat or eat cold the next day.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt; dredge in flour.
Brown chops in hot oil on both sides.
Place chops in a shallow 10-inch square casserole dish.
Top with pineapple and green pepper rings. Combine next 4 ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir well. Add cornstarch mixture to chicken broth mixture.
Stir constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve over rice.

title: silvara walker's cornbread
directions: Mix together the corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add the buttermilk, soda, egg and oil.
Beat like a cake. Oil and heat iron skillet on stove top. Pour cornbread mix in skillet and bake in oven at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, mix the eggs, milk and 1/3 cup of sugar.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat.
Cool quickly by placing pan in a sink or bowl of ice water and stirring 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in rum, bourbon and vanilla.
Chill 4 to 24 hours.
When serving, top with ground nutmeg, a sprinkling of sugar and a dollop of whipping cream.

title: glazed bacon
directions: Place bacon in large baking pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes or until crisp.
Mix brown sugar, mustard and wine thoroughly.
Pour over bacon.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles, making sure the bacon glaze is covering both sides, approximately 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to wax paper or foil.
Cut bacon in half, if desired.
Do not refrigerate, but let stand at room temperature until ready to serve.
Should be dry, not sticky.

title: beef choufleur
directions: Brown meat in oleo for 5 minutes.
Add cauliflower, green pepper, soy sauce and garlic.
Stir lightly to coat with soy sauce.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and broth.
Add to meat mixture with green onions.
Cook, stirring constantly, until heated and thickened.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Brown sausage and cool.
Mix together cheeses and oregano with sausage, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Put in Miracle Whip last. Spread mixture on rye bread, sliced in 1 1/2-inch slices.
May sprinkle cheese on top.
Broil 2 minutes.

title: spanish custard or flan
directions: Use a tube pan or mold which can go on a burner to caramelize the sugar and then go in the oven.
Pour 1/2 cup sugar into the pan; set directly on burner on medium-low heat until sugar starts to melt.
Stir with wooden spoon to keep melting evenly.
Use hot pad to tilt pan to have caramel coat evenly the bottom and sides. Set aside.
Mix yolks, egg, sugar and milk in large bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour through sieve into caramelized sugar mold.
Discard the gook in the sieve.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes with pan in hot water, or until toothpick comes clean 1/2-inch from center.
Cool completely.
Run knife around edge; turn onto serving plate.
Keep mold upside-down on plate to allow all caramel to drip out.
Nice with strawberries or cookies.

title: super spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat
the
oil,
then brown ground beef.
After beef is brown, drain
off
fat on paper towel.
Discard oil from pan. Return beef
to
pan.
Add
the whole tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, spaghetti
sauce
mix and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until soft enough to mash; add milk as needed.
Mix remaining ingredients with mashed potatoes.
Good warm or cold.

title: spicy cocktail hot dogs
directions: In medium saucepan, heat mustard and currant jelly, stirring until the jelly melts.
Add the hot dogs and cook over low heat until ready to serve.
Place in chafing dish or fondue pot to keep hot dogs warm.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Arrange potato wedges, peel side down, in shallow baking pans. Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes or until potatoes are golden brown and tender, brushing occasionally with oil mixture.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon and save liquid.
Add enough milk to make 1 cup. Melt butter; add flour and stir until smooth.
Add liquid.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Flake salmon; add white sauce.
Then add other ingredients.
Shape into a loaf and put in a greased dish. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: nut kifle
directions: Take flour, butter and salt and mix well together.
Then add egg yolks and sour cream.
Form into small ball and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out thin and fill with
nuts or prune jelly. Fold in half and seal edges with fork teeth.
Brush egg white on top.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: country rice dressing
directions: Mix
all
of the ingredients in a pan that will be used to bake.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes, covered, at 350°. Stir before done.

title: kidney beans(monday's dinner)
directions: *Be careful not to add salt until you taste the liquid to determine what salt the seasoning meat produces.

title: macaroni and vegetable salad
directions: Add all ingredients; toss lightly.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer the ingredients in a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.

title: almond delight
directions: Combine coconut, almonds, sugar, flour and oleo.
Mix well. Put in large pan and bake at 325° until golden brown; stir every 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Line dish with crumbs.
Add pudding to milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in crumb lined bowl; top with remaining crumbs.
Chill.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box. While still warm, punch holes in cake. Pour condensed milk over cake. Put cake in refrigerator overnight (if you have time). Spread caramel over cool cake, then Cool Whip. Sprinkle cake with crushed up candy bars.

title: mom's chocolate velvet cake
directions: Combine chocolate pieces and 1/4 cup water in saucepan; stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda together; set aside.
Combine sugar, butter and vanilla in bowl; beat until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in melted chocolate mixture.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with 1 cup water.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Chocolate Velvet Frosting.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the Tang and pudding into pineapple and juice.
Add the drained peaches, bananas and strawberries.

title: shrimp potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Combine squash with sour cream, onion, egg, mushroom soup, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Top with herb stuffing.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bottom:
Prepare stuffing and 1/2 can onions.
Then add broccoli.
Add sour cream, soup, milk and chicken and pour over broccoli and stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add 1/2 onions and put on top the last 5 minutes.

title: sausage cake
directions: Separate sausage into small pieces and combine with raisins. Pour boiling water over sausage and raisins and allow to boil about 4 minutes.
Let cool and add soda.
While mixture cools, sift together flour, sugar and spices.
Sift into sausage mixture and combine well.
You may add nuts and fruits from your favorite cake recipe.
Bake 1 to 1 1/4 hours in slow oven at 300°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach well. Mix all ingredients together. Best if made 12 hours ahead of time.

title: easy taco casserole
directions: Boil pasta as directed on package. Brown hamburger meat and drain. Add tomato sauce and taco seasoning. After pasta is cooked, drain and add sour cream and 1 cup cheddar cheese and mix together.

title: vanilla and carob ice cream
directions: First place 2 cups of water into blender.
Now add all other ingredients and blend together until smooth.
Add 1 more cup of water and blend again until smooth.
Place into shallow oblong pans and partially freeze.
Blend again and refreeze.
It is now ready to serve.
It is not only delicious but also nutritious.

title: peanut candy
directions: Put in skillet and boil until peanuts start to pop.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon soda.
Pour on cookie sheet.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: Beat well cream cheese, 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla. Spread in crust.
Sprinkle with 1 1/4 cups pecans.

title: caramel sticks
directions: Melt sugar with margarine in saucepan.
Cool.
Add flour, baking powder, egg and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in an 8 to 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 30 minutes.
Cool a few minutes, then cut into fingers.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole dish in oven.
Remove from oven.
Add batter of flour, sugar, milk and cinnamon.
Do not stir.
Pour the can of peaches over the top. Do not stir.
Put the dish back into the oven.
Bake approximately 1 hour.
Remember, do not stir at any point!

title: tunaburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill buns.
Wrap in foil.
Heat in 300° oven 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve hot.
Can be made ahead and frozen individually in foil before cooking.
Thaw before heating.

title: toffee fudge
directions: Sprinkle pecans on bottom of greased square pan, 9-inch. Combine sugar and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil 7 min. remove from heat and spread over nuts. Sprinkle chocolate pieces over top.
Cover pan so heat will melt chocolate.
Spread evenly over top.
Cut in squares while warm. Refrigerate to set.
Makes 36 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour; beat well, then add nuts, pineapple, coconut and flavoring.
Grease tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at about 350°.

title: chinese noodles
