directions: Saute vegetables in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add remaining ingredients and put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until heated.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix together and add about 8 ounces Green Goddess dressing (enough to hold mix together).
Add Tabasco sauce to taste (just a shake or two).
Chill.
Serve with nacho style chips.

title: chocolate chipper cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and pecan halves.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter into 13 x 9-inch pan (greased on bottom only).
Sprinkle chips and nuts over batter. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° or until cake springs back in center.
Serve plain or with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: lemonade pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, condensed milk and frozen lemonade, partly thawed.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool at room temperature.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; combine until smooth.
For variety, add a dash of dill weed or tarragon.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Steam onion and zucchini for 5 minutes.
Melt butter; mix with stuffing.
Add sour cream and undiluted soup to zucchini and onion.
Put half of the stuffing in a baking dish.
add the zucchini and layer the remaining dressing on top.
Sprinkle with the grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: freezer jelly
directions: Mix berries, sugar and lemon; let stand for 10 minutes. Dissolve 1 box Sure-Jell with 3/4 cup water; stir well, bring to rolling boil for 1 minute.
Combine berry mixture and Sure-Jell; bring to hard rolling boil (blend froth in).
Let stand for 15 minutes, stirring every 4 to 5 minutes.
Put in jar or dish, 1-inch from top.
Cover.
Let stand 24 hours.
Store in freezer.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook until tender in stock.

title: jubilee jumbles
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: happy pumpkin bread(24 slices; a low sugar recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place pumpkin, frozen fruit juice concentrate, water, whole mashed banana and vanilla in a mixing bowl and blend well.
Sift together flours, baking soda, baking powder, pumpkin pie spice, cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: ice cream roll
directions: Beat the eggs, flour, cinnamon, 2/3 cup sugar and baking powder.
Then add 3 tablespoons sugar, soda, vegetable oil, water and cocoa.
Put in a jelly roll pan lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
When done, take out on a tea towel and roll up until cool, then unroll and spread ice cream on it.
Roll up, wrap in foil and put in freezer.
We like chocolate mint ice cream!
Slice to serve.

title: round steak and potatoes
directions: Cut round steak into cubes and coat with flour.
Brown in skillet with onion until tender.
Place into greased casserole. Sprinkle with flour, salt, pepper, thyme and garlic.
Pour 2 cups hot water over meat and bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Then add sliced potatoes on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed; pour half of mix in bottom of pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels in a double boiler and mix with butter and Pet milk.
Pour over baked cake and sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour rest of cake mix over this and bake for about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate mocha dream
directions: Put coffee and chocolate bar in blender.
Cover and run on liquefy until chocolate is liquified.
Add bourbon and ice cream. Cover and run on blend until smooth.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl. Bake at 350° in greased oblong cake pan.

title: pronto chili
directions: In a saucepan, brown beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese; cover and simmer 20 minutes. Top each serving with cheese, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: nut and poppy seed rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and set aside.
Sift flour, sugar and salt into a bowl.
Cut in shortening and gradually add well beaten eggs.
Blend then gradually add the dissolved yeast and once again blend thoroughly.
Place in the refrigerator overnight. Next day, divide dough into 7 or 8 parts.
Roll out each part on floured board and spread with nut or poppy seed mixture and roll. Place on greased baking sheet and let stand for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peter paul mounds cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Stir in the flour alternately with the milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 4 cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Combine dates, 1/2 cup sugar, water and nuts.
Cook and stir approximately 5 minutes.
(You may want to add a little more water.)
Let cool.
In a large mixing bowl mix sugars, shortening, eggs, soda, salt and flour to make dough.
Roll dough out on a floured board.
Spread date mixture onto rolled dough.
Then roll into 2 rolls and put in refrigerator to chill.
Cut cookies off to bake.
Place cookies on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: guiltless banana pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, whisk or beat milk and pudding mix until thickened. Fold in whipped topping, condensed milk and lemon juice. Layer half of the vanilla wafers, half the bananas and half the pudding mixture in an 8-inch square glass dish, glass serving dish or individual bowls; repeat. Put plastic wrap directly on surface of pudding and refrigerate. Serves 8 (1 cup per serving).

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water. Cook until thick.
Gradually stir mixture into beaten egg yolks. Return to low heat and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in butter, lime juice and rind and cook slightly.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.

title: coconut joys
directions: Melt butter; add powdered sugar and coconut, then mix well. Press into buttered cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over coconut mixture.
Chill and cut into squares for serving.

title: texas quick dip
directions: In medium-sized bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream.
Fold in salsa.
Store in refrigerator, but serve at room temperature.
Serve with chips or vegetables.

title: peach pie
directions: Put the butter in a deep pan and melt in oven.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Add fruit with juice and bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: a magic garden
directions: Crumple the aluminum foil into an uneven mountain-like shape. Place it in the dish so that it covers the bottom.
Stir the mix well; pour it slowly over the crumpled foil.
Be sure that some of the salt is on most of the foil.
You can put food coloring in it, but you have to put it in as soon as you pour it in.

title: texas sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Line with sliced potatoes and fruit.
Combine 1 cup of reserved syrup from drained fruit with sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and orange peel.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add butter and nuts.
Pour over potatoes and fruit.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Set aside.
Beat eggs with electric mixer at medium speed, until frothy.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar to eggs.
Beat until thick.
Add salt, vanilla extract, and 1/2 cup milk.
Beat, until sugar has dissolved.
Stir in whipped cream, half-and-half, and peach mixture.
Pour mixture into freezer cylinder of a 1-gallon ice cream maker.
Add enough milk to fill can 2/3 full.
Freeze according to manufacturer instructions.
Let ripen 1 hour.

title: summer salad
directions: Cut just the very tops of broccoli and cabbage. Slice carrots bite size.
Shake and pour dressing over all and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Slice the raw sweet potatoes 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Put them in a Corning Ware or Pyrex dish 2 inches deep, in layers, staggering rows not more than 3 layers.
On each layer, alternate sprinkling a little salt and sugar (you add between 1 to 1 1/2 cups).
After this is done, pour the unbeaten whipping cream over the potatoes, filling the pan 3/4 full.
Put pats of butter or margarine over the top.
Bake in preheated 350° to 375° oven for 3/4 to 1 hour.
They should be nice and brown and caramelized.

title: perfect orange nut bread
directions: Mix first 4 items; add remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 70 minutes. Cover with another pan the first 20 minutes so loaf won't crack on the top.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in floured tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese bars
directions: Slightly beat first 5 ingredients.
Cook in microwave until thick, then add remaining ingredients.
Cool.
Pour into your baked pie crust.
Add meringue.
Bake.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Mix for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: stuffed chicken breast with crab
directions: *If you choose to leave out the mayonnaise, you can substitute it for melted cheese of your choice. I prefer Colby Jack cheese.

title: glorified shortbread
directions: Cut butter into mixture of next 4 ingredients until crumbly. Press into 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Combine confectioners sugar, orange juice and rind in bowl. Spread on shortbread.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Top each wedge with 1 walnut half.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: mammy's corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; stir in dry ingredients, margarine and milk. Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Set dish in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion, bell pepper, celery, 6 chopped boiled eggs, 1/2 bacon bits and 1/2 cheese in large casserole dish, add on top frozen peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour over top of peas, spread to make smooth.
Slice remaining eggs, lay on top, spread remaining cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
The longer it sits, the better.
You can use low-fat shredded cheese and low-fat bacon bits and the flavor will not be effected.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onions (very thin).
Boil in water until tender.
Drain water and add margarine and milk.
Heat until just hot, do not boil.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes; add remaining ingredients.
Spread in well-greased cookie sheet and sprinkle 3/4 cup nuts on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn out on a towel well dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll as for a jelly roll.
Wait 5 minutes and unroll and spread with filling.

title: honey lemon chicken
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in shallow baking dish.
Stir until well blended.
Place chicken in marinade.
Turn to coat. Refrigerate 30 minutes; turn once.
Heat broiler or prepare grill. Remove chicken from marinade.
Broil or grill 3 to 5 minutes per side.

title: tex-mex tamale skillet(prep time: 30 minutes)
directions: Brown beef in skillet over medium-high heat. Drain. Add salsa, corn and tortilla strips; mix well. Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with cheese; cover and cook an additional 5 minutes, until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with cilantro.

title: lemon-carrot tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place loaf baking cups in pan.
Cream butter and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder; toss with fork to combine.
Combine milk and lemon juice.
Add alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Start and end with milk.
Mix only until ingredients are moistened.
Mix in lemon rind, pecans and carrots.
Place 1/2 cup batter (fill cavities approximately half full) in each pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes. Cool 5 minutes, remove from pans, cool completely and wrap.
May be frozen 2 months.
Serve cool.
Makes 18 small loaves or use 2 bigger pans.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet over moderate heat, saute onion, celery and broccoli in butter for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk until smooth.
Place rice in a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over rice, do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Makes a delicious complement to any meat or fish dish as well as being attractive on the table.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and onions in a large size bag and add oil. Toss to coat. Add dressing mix and toss again until coated. Bake on an ungreased baking pan for 35 minutes at 450° or until potatoes are tender. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: egg pie
directions: Beat egg whites and add to mixture last.
Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Makes 1 pie.

title: dream cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat 2 minutes.
Pour in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Use same kind of pudding mix as cake mix.

title: hot 'n' heavenly chicken breasts
directions: Dredge chicken in seasoned flour.
In medium frying pan, melt margarine with onion and garlic.
Add chicken and saute until lightly brown.
Add bouillon cube, mixed with water, and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine sour cream, lemon juice and picante sauce.
Pour over chicken; simmer, heating through.
Serve over angel hair pasta.
Serves 4.

title: apple relish(for canning)
directions: Put all ingredients through food grinder.
Cook 25 minutes. Put in clean jars and seal lids.
Turn upside down until cold. Store for later use.

title: grits au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring salted water to boil; slowly stir in grits.
Cover, reduce heat and cook, stirring occasionally until liquid is absorbed, according to package instructions.
Remove from heat.
Whisk eggs slightly; then stir in small amount of grits to warm them.
Beat egg mixture into grits.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour grits mixture into greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: basic biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Blend in enough milk to make a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead gently 30 seconds. Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits with floured 2-inch biscuit cutter or sharp knife.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in preheated 450° oven 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: orange-cranberry cheese cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and grated orange rind in bowl.
Add butter, egg yolk and vanilla.
Cut in with pastry blender and then knead with fingers until smooth.
Pat 1/3 of dough over bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Pat enough remaining dough evenly around sides to 1/2-inch from top.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: catfish stew
directions: You also need a 3 to 5-gallon metal pot.

title: easter swirl coffee bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water and let stand until dissolved. With an electric mixer, cream the butter until light and beat in sugar. Beat in egg yolks, then add yeast mixture, milk, salt and cardamon. Gradually mix in the flour, beating at low speed or by hand.
Dough will be quite soft. Turn out on a floured board and knead until smooth. Return dough to bowl and butter the top lightly.
Cover and let rise in a warm place about 1 1/2 hours.

title: french cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish in preheated oven.
In a medium-sized bowl, mix flour, 1 cup granulated sugar, baking powder and milk together.
Pour over the melted margarine in the baking pan.
Place the sliced, fresh fruit on top of the batter.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup granulated sugar and optional cinnamon over the fruit.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until the top is golden brown.
This is excellent served with vanilla ice cream.

title: zucchini beef skillet
directions: Saute beef, onion, green pepper and garlic in 12-inch skillet until well browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix marinade ingredients together.
Pour over flank steak and let marinate for at least 2 hours.

title: red potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes, leaving part of skin intact.
Cut in wedges. Mix all ingredients and place in plastic sealed bag; let set at least an hour.
Spray casserole dish (2-quart) with nonstick cooking spray.
Place all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine pineapple and cheese.
Add flour and sugar.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs and pour margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and cook until the right thickness for you.

title: baked italian macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring macaroni to boil in boiler pot (do not overcook); drain.
Grate Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar (put in separate pans).
Cut olives in half (place to side); drain off liquid.
Open mushrooms and drain.

title: poppy seed dressing(origin:  usa - southern)
directions: Place first five ingredients in a blender and mix.
Add oil slowly and beat until thick.
Stir in poppy seed by hand. Use for all fruit salads, finely shredded cabbage or sliced avocados.

title: honey of a cornbread
directions: In a medium bowl, thoroughly mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
In another bowl, whisk the egg whites until frothy.
Whisk in skim milk, yogurt and honey.
Pour over the dry ingredients.
Stir until all the dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix.
Coat an 8 x 8-inch baking pan with no-stick spray.
Pour the batter into the pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: millie's 8 minute cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth, gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill.
Garnish, if desired.

title: cinnamon squares
directions: Mix all together except nuts.
Spread out on cookie sheet. Spread pecans over dough.
Take egg white (not whipped) and brush over the top.
Mash nuts down in dough.
Bake at 325° until brown. Cut as soon as you take out of oven and take up on wax paper to cool.

title: society pickles
directions: From the North Dakota Jaycees, July, 1976.

title: party mints
directions: Soften butter and add milk, peppermint and coloring.
Sift sugar; mix, then knead with hands.
Mold as desired.
Let dry on wax paper 12 hours.
Can freeze in tightly sealed container.

title: swiss chicken(very easy and quick)
directions: Pound chicken and dip in bread crumbs (plain).
Sprinkle lemon pepper seasoning over it.
Melt butter or oil over medium heat and brown chicken, then drain and line in dish.
Pour sauce over chicken and cut tomato wedges for top of each piece.
Lay Swiss cheese over each piece.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican potato salad
directions: Combine ingredients in the order given; chill and serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 6.

title: baby wipes
directions: Great for gifts, bazaars, bake sales, craft shows!
Read all instructions before beginning.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix Knox gelatine, sugar and salt; gradually stir in eggnog. Warm over low heat until Knox gelatine is dissolved.
Chill until mixture folds well.
Fold in whipped cream, flavoring and 1 1/2 cups fruit cocktail.
Chill again 5 to 10 minutes, until mixture mounds.
Heap into pie shell.
Decorate with remaining fruit cocktail.
Chill 2 to 4 hours.

title: enchilada casserole(serves 6 to 8 people)
directions: Layer in casserole dish in order listed (ground beef, beans, soup, tortillas, cheese and Ro-Tel).
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot dinner
directions: Place soup, chicken, thyme and sweet potatoes in crock-pot. Cook on medium 1 hour and on low 5 to 6 hours, adding peas in last hour of cooking.

title: banana blueberry pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix well with sugar.
Bake pie crust and let cool.
Beat whipping cream with vanilla until stiff; fold whipped cream into cheese and sugar mixture.
Line bottom of pie crust with sliced bananas.
Put cheese and whipped cream filling on top of bananas.
Spread pie filling on top of whipped cream. Chill.

title: ground deer steaks
directions: Put deer meat in a steel mixing bowl or glass and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and make into patties.
Roll patties in ground cracker crumbs.
Can place on wax paper and store in refrigerator until ready to cook.
Fry in electric skillet at 350° until lightly brown and done.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix together in a large sealable bag. Add meat and seal. Keep refrigerated.
Turn to coat all meat every 15 minutes for 1 hour or less.
Drain meat and cook on grill as desired.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli in a little water until thawed; drain.
In another pan, melt cheese, soup and lemon juice, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli to cheese mixture.
Serve with the big Fritos.

title: german chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press in the bottom of a 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.

title: ricotta mix for giant shells or manicotti
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Cook 1 pound of the shells or manicotti in boiling water for 5 to 6 minutes.
Pasta must be on the hard side.
Drain and run cold water on it.
Pour some of your favorite spaghetti sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Use a spoon or pastry bag to fill each shell or manicotti with cheese mixture. Place side by side in baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over (as much as desired).
Sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender; remove from skillet and set aside.
Add beef to skillet; saute until brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, marjoram, thyme, bouillon and cooking wine. Cover and cook over low heat 3 hours.
Stir in mushrooms and sauteed onion.
Serve over noodles.
Can be served over rice.

title: the punch
directions: Mix ingredients together, reserving club soda until ready to serve.
This is a "not too sweet" punch that gets rave notices.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped nuts and bananas. Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tests done.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top and sides.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: outrageous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, oleo, peanut butter, vanilla and eggs until creamy and well blended.
Mix in flour, oatmeal, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until light golden brown.

title: okra soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except okra, in large pot.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Keep enough water on vegetables to look "soupy."
Then add okra and simmer about 4 or 5 minutes longer.

title: brisket marinade
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over both sides of brisket that has been placed in a large plastic bag.
Close bag tightly and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Cook as desired.
Recommended:
cook for 4 hours in a 300° oven.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Combine in mixing bowl all ingredients except whipping cream. Spoon into greased 9 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipping cream and a cold glass of milk.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Pour the boiling coffee over the cocoa and baking soda in a large bowl.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add cooled cocoa mixture.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados; add garlic, salt, lemon juice, Worcestershire and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Leave two avocado seeds in the bottom of your dip.

title: blueberry cake or muffins
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs until light.
In seperate bowl, sift flour baking powder, and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla to the egg mixture.
Add blueberries.
Pour into greased 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 min. until brown.
Sugar may be sprinkled on top.

title: miracle cheesecake
directions: Pour water over Jell-O.
Chill until slightly thickened. Cream the sugar, cheese and vanilla. Add Jell-O and lemon juice. Mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten milk.
Mix graham crackers and butter.
Press firmly in bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill overnight.

title: delta delight fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs together.
Add the sugar and cream well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla, and almond flavorings.
Add dates, cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Hand mix well.
Pack into wax paper lined, greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 250 degrees 4 to 5 hours over a pan of water.
Let cake cool completely before removing
from pan.

title: beef stew
directions: Put salt, pepper, flour and meat into paper bag and shake, being sure to coat meat well.
Brown meat in heavy skillet; drain off any grease.
Add water, broth, bay leaf, onions, tomato sauce and sherry.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: bert's fudge caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk (in double boiler or microwave); set aside.

title: kraut cake
directions: Cut or chop sauerkraut; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time, beat after each egg.
Beat in vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and cocoa, add to creamed mixture alternately, begin and end with flour.
Stir in kraut.
Bake in well greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: the "colonel's" cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage.
Add dressing to cabbage and mix well.
Serve ice cold.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Break meat
into
small
chunks;
place in slow cooker. Add all other ingredients, except beans; cover and cook on low heat for 5 hours
or high heat for 3 hours. Stir, mix in beans (including juices).
Cover
and cook 1 hour longer on low heat or 1/2 hour longer on high heat.

title: hot chicken (or turkey) salad
directions: Combine all but last 3 ingredients.
Place in buttered, 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine margarine and crumbs; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: good pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and corn syrup.
Beat well.
Blend in 1 cup pecans, salt, vinegar and butter.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until set.

title: southern fried okra salad
directions: Coat salted okra with corn meal and flour.
Fry in pan of oil. Cook to golden brown; remove, add chopped tomato and onion. Toss.

title: c.j.'s tangy bread and butter pickles
directions: Do not pare cucumbers; slice thin.
Add onions, peppers and garlic.
Add salt.
Cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and let sit 3 hours.
(I use large roaster pan.)
Drain well. Combine remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Add cucumber mixture and stir well.
Heat to boiling.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 5 quarts.
Be sure to pack cucumbers in jars.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large pan.
Do not drain grease.
Add tomato juice, beans, chili seasoning and tomato.
Let simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
If you prefer a thicker chili, add a small can of tomato paste.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs. Sift flour; add alternately with milk. Stir in syrup. Melt candy bars; add to mixture. Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients. Form into ball.
Chill.
Roll in crushed nuts.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Mix jello in 2 cups of hot water and cool in refrigerator until partially set.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together.
Add jello and lemon juice and beat well.
Stir in Cool Whip until well blended.
Add marshmallows, oranges and crushed pineapple.
You may add one cup of white grape halves also, if you wish.

title: zebra linebacker barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine meat, barbecue sauce and pepper; heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Fill rolls with meat mixture and process cheese food; wrap in foil.
Bake 10 minutes.
Makes 6 sandwiches.
Preparation time: 15 minutes. Cooking time:
10 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine and simmer the chili sauce, 1/4 cup finely grated onion and the cranberry sauce.
Combine hamburger and onion and make into 1-inch meatballs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Pour sauce over meatballs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: english toffee
directions: In a 2 to 3-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add the sugar and stir constantly over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Then add the corn syrup and continue to cook over a medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until temperature reaches 297° (do not undercook).
Remove from heat.
Add salt and nuts and gently mix in.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb with sugar.
Cool.
Dissolve jello in hot water, let cool.
Add pineapple, celery, nuts, and rhubarb.
Chill for several hours.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Place crackers in
paper
bag.	Mix
rest in a bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Shake well and serve.

title: chicken or tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put remaining noodles on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: squirrel and dumplings
directions: Salt and pepper to taste.
Put squirrels in 5-quart boiler. Cover with water and boil until tender.
Remove meat; debone and set aside.

title: apple crisp(microwave)
directions: In microwaveable pan, place apples in bottom and simply add all other ingredients on top.
Blend prior if preferred. Microwave
5 to 7 minutes on High.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Cut up cooked chicken.
Separate crescent rolls.
Place about 1 tablespoon chicken on the wide end of the crescent and roll up. Combine soup, cheese, butter, milk and pepper and heat until smooth.

Pour 1/3 of the sauce on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place chicken rolls on sauce and pour rest of the sauce over. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until tops of rolls are golden brown. Serves 10 (2 rolls each).

title: ashville salad
directions: Heat soup and cheese, then add gelatine that has been dissolved in cold water.
Add mayonnaise, celery, peppers, pecans and onion juice.
Put in oblong pan and top with sliced olives.
Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix all remaining ingredients except crumbs or crackers.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat egg yolk well.
Add sugar, butter, squash, milk, salt and cornstarch.
Mix together and add vanilla.
Over medium heat, bring mixture to a complete boil.
Pour into baked pie crust. Spoon meringue on top and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, until brown.

title: punch for a crowd(60 people)
directions: Ginger ale is added the very last minute.
Serve over ice cubes in a large punch bowl.
If necessary, add 1 ginger ale.
Get ready 1/2 hour ahead.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Using a foil casserole pan, put cooked vegetables in the bottom.
Cover with mixture of eggs, soup, milk and cheeses.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers; dab approximately 3 tablespoons margarine on top of crackers.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour until browned and bubbly.

title: chicken pie with sweet potato crust
directions: Put a layer of chicken in 2-quart baking dish, a layer of green pepper and then a layer of onions.
Sprinkle with parsley. Repeat until all vegetables are used.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directed.
Cut cake in half.
Break one half in bowl.
Add 1 box pudding mix (mixed as for pudding), 1 can crushed pineapple and 1/2 can cherry pie filling.
Then add a little Cool Whip and one sliced banana.
Then repeat with more layers of same.
Slice a banana on top; cover with Cool Whip and top with nuts.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In small bowl, blend pie filling mix, whipped topping mix, milk and vanilla on low speed of electric mixer.
Increase speed to high and beat until very thick, about 3 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of mixture into crust.
Layer slices of banana on top, reserving 1/2 banana for garnish.
Pour remaining filling into crust.
Chill until set, about 1 hour.
Garnish with banana slices and additional whipped topping, if desired.
To prevent darkening, dip banana slices for garnishing in lemon juice.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place salad in a 2-quart Pyrex oblong casserole.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven about 45 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: grilled vegetable kabobs with rice
directions: Combine dressing, parsley and basil in small bowl; cover and chill.
Alternate squash, onion, tomatoes and mushrooms on 8 skewers.
Spray grill rack with vegetable spray; place on grill over medium heat.
Place kabobs on rack and cook 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender, turning and basting frequently with dressing mixture.
Serve with 1/2 cup rice on each plate and top with 2 vegetable kabobs.
Serves 4.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg, bananas and cream.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal and walnuts.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: heavenly yogurt
directions: Spray a saute pan with nonstick cooking spray lightly.
Brown banana; add orange juice, apples and optional fruit.
Continue cooking on medium heat until apples are softened and orange juice is reduced.
Spoon over yogurt and sprinkle with granola.

title: caramel nut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and brown sugar a little at a time. Beat well.
Add white granulated sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat 3 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325°.

title: orange sauce for pork
directions: Heat ingredients, stirring to thicken and mixture is clear. Coat pork with sauce.
Also good to use as a sauce after pork is cooked.

title: lickety split banana split pie
directions: Slice bananas into bottom of crust.
Spoon softened ice cream on top.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Top with unheated hot fudge, pineapple preserves, whipped topping, chopped nuts and a maraschino cherry.

title: yogi popsicles
directions: Mix well and freeze in molds.
Three ounce paper cups work well as molds.
Insert wooden sticks or spoons for handles.

title: field mouse casserole
directions: Boil macaroni 10 minutes.
While it is being cooled, fry mice long enough to get the fat out.
Drain macaroni.
Grease casserole with the fat from the field mice.
Layer the mice, macaroni, onions and tomatoes.
Repeat layers until all are used.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until mice are well done.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss together and pour over the following combined ingredients:
